Shingles flare up; Shingles flare up; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable nurse (patient). A 31-year-old male patient received his second dose of bnt162b2 (BNT162B2 reported as PFIZER COVID VACCINE; lot number: EL9262; expiration date: unknown) at 31-year-old vaccination age via an unspecified route of administration in the right deltoid on 18Feb2021 9:00 AM as a single dose to protect self (covid-19 immunization). Medical history included chicken pox virus as a kid and shingles. The patient has no family medical history. There were no concomitant medications. Historical vaccination included varicella zoster vaccine (CHICKENPOX VACCINE) for vaccination for chicken pox and received his first dose of bnt162b2 (BNT162B2 reported as PFIZER COVID VACCINE; lot number: EL3246) at unknown vaccination age via an unspecified route of administration in the left deltoid on an unspecified date as a single dose to protect self (covid-19 immunization). The patient received the vaccine in a hospital and did not receive other vaccines administered on same date of Pfizer suspect. The patient did not have prior vaccinations within 4 weeks. The patient reported that he just got a flare up of shingles on 28Feb2021 and doesn't know if it is related or not to the covid vaccination he took. The patient reported that he did nothing unusual in the last 14 days. Doesn't know if that is something to report to see if there was any trending. The patient inquired if a shingles flare-up has happened before after the COVID vaccine. He got the vaccine ten days before (18Feb2021) the shingles flare up started. He added that it is on right side of torso in the thorax area and goes from midline abdomen all the way to midline on his back on the right side. The adverse event required urgent care visit (emergency room visit). The nurse considered the event serious. The patient did not have relevant tests and was only clinically diagnosed with a shingles flare up. The outcome of the events was not recovered.; Sender's Comments: Based on the information currently available, a possible contributory role of the suspect drug to the reported event "Shingles flare up" cannot be completely excluded based on temporal association.   The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identifies as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notifies to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committees and Investigators, as appropriate.

it was like someone was jumping up and down on his cheast/then pain went down left arm/heart attack; felt like his eyes were spinning in his head; cold sweats; myopericarditis; This spontaneous report was received from a 64 year old male consumer reporting on himself. The patient's concurrent conditions included allergy to nitrates and nitroglycerin. There was no pertinent medical history. On 27-SEP-2017, the patient was vaccinated with a dose of pneumococcal vaccine, polyvalent (23-valent) (PNEUMOVAX23) (dose and route not reported) in the left arm. Concomitant therapies included vitamins and supplements.     The patient reported that he received the influenza virus vaccine (unspecified) in the right arm twenty minutes prior  pneumococcal vaccine, polyvalent (23-valent) (PNEUMOVAX23). He stated that immediately after the vaccine was given, he said to his wife "something was wrong" it was like his eyes were spinning in his head. The patient stated that he had cold sweats and was told to sit for a few minutes, but he went home. The patient reported that the next day on 28-SEP-2017, he went to the emergency room for 4-5 hours where they tested everything and gave him "intravenous" and was sent home. The consumer reported that two weeks later, on 10-OCT-2017 at 2:00am he woke up and said it was like someone was jumping up and down on his chest. He went to the bathroom, got a glass of water and then pain went down left arm. The patient went to emergency room again and they did blood tests which included troponin levels (first one was zero, second one was 1.38 and third one was higher). The patient was told that he had a heart attack and was admitted for five days. The patient additionally stated that during hospital stay they did a catherization, no blockages, but had inflammation around heart (myopericarditis) and inflammation of lining of heart and muscle. The patient reported that the only reason they said it was a heart attack was because of enzyme on blood test levels were high. The patient was scared to get the Covid vaccine, so this was why he wanted to find out the ingredients of pneumococcal vaccine, polyvalent (23-valent) (PNEUMOVAX23) to compare. At the time of the report, the patient had recovered.  The causality between the events and pneumococcal vaccine, polyvalent (23-valent) (PNEUMOVAX23) was unknown.  Upon internal review heart attack and myopericarditis were considered to be medically significant.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Possible Carpal tunnel syndrome; inflammation everywhere in his body / inflammation in glutes, thighs, back of knees, bottom of feet, neck and shoulders; The pain in his hands ebbs and flows / pain presented in his hands and wrists; muscle aches everywhere /  The aches progressively became worse as time went on; aches are present everywhere else / aches; it feels like a storm is going on inside his body; feels burning all over his body; stomach is burning as well; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of carpal tunnel syndrome in a 54-year-old male patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   Concomitant products included Flu Seasonal QIV Dresden (Influenza vaccine Quadrivalent 2019-2020 season) and Herpes zoster (Shingrix).   In October 2020, the patient received the 2nd dose of Shingrix. On an unknown date, less than 2 months after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced carpal tunnel syndrome, inflammation, pain in hand, muscle pain, general body pain, feeling abnormal, burning sensation and stomach burning sensation of. On an unknown date, the outcome of the carpal tunnel syndrome, general body pain, feeling abnormal, burning sensation and stomach burning sensation of were unknown and the outcome of the inflammation, pain in hand and muscle pain were not recovered/not resolved.   It was unknown if the reporter considered the carpal tunnel syndrome, inflammation, pain in hand, muscle pain, general body pain, feeling abnormal, burning sensation and stomach burning sensation of to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: The patient had his first dose of Shingrix in one arm and a flu shot in the other arm at the same time in August 2020.   The patient was administered the 2nd dose of Shingrix exactly 2 months after the first. The exact vaccination dates were unknown. In either October or November the patient started to feel inflammation everywhere in his body. Then pain presented in his hands and wrists followed by muscle aches everywhere. At first it was thought to be carpool tunnel syndrome.   The pain in his hands ebbs and flows but the aches were present everywhere else. The aches progressively became worse as time went on. At the time of reporting , he had aches and inflammation in glutes, thighs, back of knees, bottom of feet, neck and shoulders. He said it feels like a storm was going on inside his body. There were aches everywhere with the exception of his head and ears.   In other words, he was symptom free from the chin up. The patient stated that the patient felt burning all over his body. He stated his stomach was burning as well. The reporter consented to follow up. The pharmacist provided permission to follow up with her for additional details such as the lot numbers of both the Shingrix and the Flu vaccine.

On March 5, I received my first dose of the Covid shot. Later that day, I was fatigued.  Six days later, however, sometime early morning on March 12, (I was in and out of sleep because of it), I had pain swallowing my saliva on my left side (also the side of my vaccine in my arm). It was hard to pinpoint but the pain came from somewhere at the back of my throat and my ear. If I had to guess what time it was, it probably was around 1-2am that the pain began. March 12, I went to see my primary care doctor. He checked my ears & didn't see any concern. He saw a little redness at the back of my throat but couldn't definitively say what I had. He thought it was a virus but didn?t discount a reaction to the vaccine (although he said it was unlikely since reactions usually happen within 3 days). He ran no tests and didn't prescribe anything.  March 13, I was feeling worse. I suddenly had a fever (101 was the highest it ever got), swollen lymph nodes, a white tongue. I went to the local ER at 9am who said I might have oral thrush but he didn?t sound convinced because my tongue wasn't as white o thick as thrush would present (he said for example that typically when you have thrush, you could scrap it off and it would bleed). He diagnosed me with Thrush and Lymphadenopathy. He prescribed anti-fungus medication Clotrimazole 10 mg Troche, five times a day. On Sunday, March 14, my throat pain got worse (it was constant pain v.s. pain only swallowing) so I called the on-call doc who told me to get tested for Strep.  The next day, on March 15, I could swallow easier so my doctor didn't think it was necessary. My lymph nodes were still swollen, I had a bit of a fever, and it was still a bit hard to swallow but I was recovering. I had some lingering ear pain.  By March 15 I was much better.  Today, March 19, I still have a sensation on my left ear/throat area after swallowing but I am much better. Please note that while the ER doctor thought it was fungal and my primary care doctor thought it was viral, neither were sure/thought it was the vaccine.   ** Also please note, this is the second time I am completing this because the system booted me off after 20 min the first time and it was erased. It takes times to complete. Just a thought for future reference, it might be helpful to allow for more time.**
CUR_ILL: I was treated for a staph infection by my dermatologist who prescribed antibiotics.

LAB_DATA: I emailed Dr. on 3/16/21.   After reviewing my lab results from earlier in March, she instructed me to suspend taking for 10 days:  --Liothyronine 25 mcg tablet (we had increased dosage by 5 mcg in late December) -- D3 (my levels were high, for the first time ever).   She did not feel the problem was due to thyroid medication, but decided to go ahead with this treatment.  My pulse was 82 BPM on 3/17 and 75 BPM 3/18. Today's readings are 130/81 and 79 BPM.  It is probably not related to the vaccine, but I've never had rapid heartbeat like this before and thought it was worth reporting in case others were experiencing similar symptoms.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 20 hours after injection, I had mild flu-like symptoms, including headache and muscle ache, lasting about 12 hours. But about 5 days after my injection (5 days + 5 hours, actually), I experienced a bewildering all-over rash that freaked me out. It started as itching around my elbows and ankles -- it felt like mosquito bites and sunburn together -- and spread to wrist and knee areas. The rash climbed by legs and arms. I applied coat after coat of Benadryl, which seemed to help. The rash would disappear and move somewhere else. I had it on my left foot, but then that resolved, only to find it on my right foot. After about 3 hours, it had spread to my stomach, the bridge of my nose, and my cheeks. It started to calm down around midnight. I woke up at 6:00 am (12 hours after onset) with extremely itchy hands. At 8:00 am (14 hours after onset), it had mostly disappeared except for patches on my back, and my wrists still itch. I'm hoping it goes away later today! It was crazy!

I didn't feel well, nothing specific, just generally not well.  I took 600 mg. ibuprofen.  Backache lasted all day.  Feb. 6 terrible backache continued, and I had slight headache; again generally feeling unwell.  Continued taking ibuprofen - 600 mg 2 to 3 times/day. Feb. 7, backache was better, and I had non-stop minor headache all day.  My temp. is normally around 97; that day it was 98.3. Feb. 8 backache was better, minor headache continued throughout the day, and general feeling of not being well.  Feb. 9 I finally felt better, but 2 hours after getting up in the morning, I was overwhelmingly tired.  I laid down and slept for 3 hours.  When I got up I felt better, but was exhausted all day.  I went to bed at 10:30 pm and slept through the night until 7:00 the next morning, and felt fine.  I didn't think this was a reaction to the vaccination until a friend told me one of her coworkers had COVID and it started with a backache.

At the time of the event, the patient had ongoing Asthma.  The patient's past medical history included food allergy as reported that patient had allergy to shellfish.  The patient's past vaccination(s) included FLUZONE QUADRIVALENT with no reported adverse reactions.  The patient past medical treatment(s), concomitant medication(s) and family history were not provided.  On an unknown date (two seasons ago), the patient received a dose of suspect INFLUENZA QUADRIVALENT RECOMBINANT VACCINE [lot number and expiry date not reported] via unknown route in an unknown administration site for prophylactic vaccination.  On an unknown date, the patient developed a serious laryngeal edema (laryngeal oedema) 20-30 minutes following the administration of INFLUENZA QUADRIVALENT RECOMBINANT VACCINE. This event was assessed as medically significant.  No laboratory data reported.  The patient treatment included self-treatment of 20mg of LORATADINE (CLARITINE) (CLARITHROMYCIN) and a rescue inhaler.  The patient recovered from  the event laryngeal oedema.  Information regarding the batch number of the suspect need to be requested.; Sender's Comments: This case concerns a male patient of unknown age who presented with laryngeal oedema after vaccination with FLUBLOK QIV. There is, however, no information regarding concomitant medication, past medical treatment and laboratory tests ruling out alternate etiologies. Based upon the reported information, the role of the suspect vaccine cannot be assessed.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Couldn't use thumb; Numbness; A lot of pain; Cannot raise arm above the eye or shoulder level; Outside of the injection site has become hard; I can feel a knot; Needle was inserted way down into the triceps and nowhere close to the deltoid muscle; A spontaneous report was received from a nurse who was a 61-year-old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and who experienced needle was inserted way down into the triceps and nowhere close to the deltoid muscle/incorrect route of product administration, couldn't use thumb/ limb injury, a lot of pain/pain, numbness/hypoesthesia, injection site has become hard/ injection site induration and unable to raise arm above eye or shoulder level/ injected limb mobility decreased.   The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported.    On 17-FEB-2021., prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch: 030M20A) in her left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 19-Feb-2021, She reported that there was an administration error wherein the needle was inserted about two inches above the elbow into the triceps and was nowhere near the deltoid muscle. She stated that the the patient experienced pain in thumb and could not use it, numbness, outside of the injection site become hard, knot and could not raise her arm above shoulder level.    No laboratory details were provided.  No treatment information was provided.   Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported.   The outcome of the event, needle was inserted way down into the triceps, was considered resolved.  The outcomes of the events, couldn't use thumb, a lot of pain, numbness, injection site has become hard and unable to raise arm above eye or shoulder level, were considered unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This report refers to a case of incorrect route of product administration for mRNA-1273 (lot # 030M20A) with  associated AEs reported.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Dizzy; short term memory sucks and it's frustrating; Can't see well; Fibromyalgia; bone pain; Neuropathy; Feeling aches in the body; Bells palsy-paralysis on the left side of the face/ pressure on the left side of the face and neck; headache; Ringing in the ears; Pressure in the ears; A spontaneous report was received from consumer concerning a 41-year-old, male patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced pressure in ears/ear discomfort, ringing in ears/tinnitus,  pressure on the left side of the face and neck which was found to be Bell's Palsy/facial paralysis, Headache, neuropathy peripheral, fibromyalgia, memory impairment, couldn't see well/visual decrease, feeling aches in the body/myalgia, and dizziness.  The patient's medical history included neuropathy and fibromyalgia and past cancer. No relevant concomitant medications were reported.   On 03 Feb 2021, the patient received the first of two doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 028L20A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 24FEB2021 the patient began experiencing pressure and a ringing in the ears and then started like a pressure on the left side of the face and neck. On 25FEB2021, the patient started having a  headache and on 26FEB2021 the paralysis on the left side of the face began. The patient said that it worsened, couldn't eat, couldn't speak, and went to the hospital. The patient said that they had a CT Scan, and the result was that it wasn't a stroke. Vitals were taken and blood work came back normal.  The conclusion was Bell's Palsy.  The patient stated that they couldn't see well and were dizzy.  The patient said that they were experiencing fibromyalgia and neuropathy that they had when they had cancer.  The patient also mentioned that they were experiencing some bone pain and that their short term memory was not good and was frustrating.    Treatment of these events were not reported.  The outcome of the events, ear discomfort, tinnitus, facial paralysis, headache, neuropathy peripheral, fibromyalgia, memory impairment, visual decrease, myalgia and dizziness were considered unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. A 75-year-old female patient received BNT162B2 (BNT162B2), dose 1 via an unspecified route of administration, administered in Arm Left on 06Feb2021 (Batch/Lot Number: EN9581) as SINGLE DOSE for covid-19 immunisation. I am what you call a "long hauler". I had covid in Mar2020 and every month I have the same symptoms 3 days to 15 days in each month. On the 20th between the 2 covid shots I got a very bad sickness and I don't know if it was covid19 again or the regular flu. I had the same symptoms. I'm currently recovering from that. I had SARS when I lived there in 2005 and 2008. I had chicken flu and I was really sick with both of them. I recovered and I'm fine. and I'm wondering if I had those two previously in the past history, if it's causing me to have more severe symptoms, due to osteoporosis and an auto immune disease. SYMPTOM_TEXT: About 9:30 PM on March 17, 2021 (the day that the vaccine was administered), patient began experiencing chills with shivering. Went to bed shortly thereafter. Felt weak and temporarily dizzy each time of getting out of bed. Awoke at one point with a headache, so took one Excedrin migraine tablet. Took a second Excedrin migraine tablet later in the morning of March 18, 2021, since headache persisted. Other than that, took no other prescriptions or supplements until the evening of March 18, 2021. Throughout March 18, 2021, patient felt occasional periods of weakness and took bedrest for it. Probably slept an additional 3 to 4 hours during the day. By evening of March 18, 2021, patient was feeling more normal. On March 19, 2021, patient experienced no adverse effects.

PRIOR_VAX: Occasional mild events similar to episode described in this report.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: pt states about 5 minutes after taking the covid vax she started swelling on the left inside of her throat and then she noticed the swelling was moving up towards her face around her eyes and ears then back down towards her mouth. About 20 minutes later she started feeling light headed and noticed some swelling in the right side of her throat and also experienced some discomfort on the right side of her body and had some chest tightening.  She started having SOB and could feel her tongue swelling.  Her blood pressure started going up.  She was given 50cc Benadryl.  Pt was transported by wheelchair to ER.  Her BP 160/88, pulse was 79 and respiration was 18.  Temp was 97.1.  She had a normal EKG, normal Chest X-ray normal blood work.  She was administered a steroid shot and given an IV.  She was monitored and released to FU w/ PCP and advised not to take 2nd dose.  Pt is waiting for her doctor to receive ER records to schedule FU appt.  Pt still has some sensation on the left side of her face.
HISTORY: Fibromyalgia, allergies, migraines, anemia, osteoarthritis, high cholesterol, Herpes Simplex 1,
PRIOR_VAX: Flu Vax 2018- pt had light headiness, dizziness, weakness that lasted for one month.  pt was advised not to get another flu vax.

My reaction to the vaccine was: Complete and utter fatigue, going from the bed to the bathroom and back felt like I had run a marathon, I had brain fog, headache and a temperature.  I ached all over and my vision was somewhat affected.  The idea of eating took too much energy.  No one I have talked to had a reaction like mine.  I believe there is a connection between my reaction and the Valley Fever.  I would like to know if other Valley Fever survivors had similar reactions.  After 36 hours like that, I feel much better.
OTHER_MEDS: Omega 3, Red Yeast Rice statin, Vit. D
HISTORY: I was diagnosed with Valley Fever in December of 2018. The doctor said my immune system would take care of it.  I was miserable for about three months with a painful chronic cough.  I developed antibodies after one month and the doctor declared me healed.  I asked about my cough and he said give it another six weeks.  Eventually the painful cough subsided but not the cough itself.  I continued coughing for over a year.  I went to ENT people and they didn't know why I was still coughing.  My lungs were in great shape.  The coughing finally stopped in December of 2020. I finally felt totally healed from that.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Dr. ordered the following vaccinations for patient: DTap-IPV-Hib, Hep B, Prevnar 13, and Rotarix.  Patient was given the Hep A (Havrix) vaccination instead of the Hep B (Recombivax) vaccination. The medical assistant discovered her mistake immediately when documenting the vaccination in the EMR. The medical assistant immediately informed the Dr. of her medication administration error. The medical assistant then explained to mom what had occurred. The Dr. also then spoke to the mom. Dr. explained that the Hepatitis A vaccination is usually given to children 12 months of age and up. She explained the vaccine should not harm the baby in any way, but patient would still need to receive the Hepatitis A vaccine at age 12 months and up and she still needs her second Hepatitis B vaccine. The mother was understandably very upset. She began to speak very loudly, screaming , and became agitated. This alerted security. Security advised the mother she could talk to the clinic manager. The mother left the building. Shortly afterward, the mother retuned to the building with the baby's father and other family members. The family spoke with our Chief Operating Officer. This RN attempted to call mother on Wednesday to follow-up. Mother hung up on RN x 3. RN spoke with the father Wednesday. He stated, "Patient is more sleepy than usual, but otherwise fine." This RN attempted again to call the mother and father on Thursday to follow-up. RN was unable to reach either parent. The medical assistant has been counseled. Medication rights and responsibilities have been reviewed with the MA. Vaccination safety has been reviewed with the MA.

Please see the entry in item for allergies.  The adverse event was mild hemolysis. Symptoms were unexplained back pain approximately two days after the injection; at about 1 week after injection, sharp pain in the area of the spleen along with unexplained fatigue in exercising and my left fingers and toes turned purplish.
OTHER_MEDS: Vitamin D3, Total Daily One without iron (multivitamin/multimineral), fish oil, and flax oil supplements.
HISTORY: As noted above, I have some as yet not formally diagnosed condition that causes my red blood cells to be vulnerable to oxidation from substances I've found identified on avoid lists for persons with G6PD deficiency.
PRIOR_VAX: Vertigo/spinning and illness 2 days, flucelvax. I don't recall date.
ALLERGIES: Most medications and anesthesias, and many foods and viruses, have oxidized my red blood cells, i.e., hemolysis. The degree varies with the substance, with artificial substances (medications, anesthesias, blue food dye and mothballs) being the worst,  My condition seems to either be, or act like, G6PD deficiency; to date, it is not more specifically diagnosed.  I have not sought help or treatment from the medical community because with the exception of anesthesias (whose effect is immediate), the symptoms are delayed.  The symptoms are unexplained, sudden back pain -- from blue food dye, within a few hours.  From most drugs and foods, a day or two later.  At about 1 week from the event/ingestion, sharp unexplained pain in the area of the spleen, unexplained fatigue especially in exercising, and my left toes and fingers turn purplish to bluish (cyanosis).  This is the pattern that occurred after the COVID-19 vaccine: two days later, unexplained back pain; 1 week after the vaccine, sharp pain the area of the spleen, fatigue in exercising, and my left toes and fingers turned purplish.  Given that these symptoms did not occur more immediately, I would bet that it is the COVID-19 spike virus itself that caused the hemolysis, not the other substances in the vaccine. But obviously, I don't know that for certain hence I'm reporting the adverse reaction.  This is all in addition to having an otherwise moderate reaction of the sort already known to the vaccine in terms of chills, needing to sleep, mild nausea and joint/muscle pain.

I recognize the symptoms as the same symptoms I get when I've had morphine, which I now must list as an allergy.  This lasted 4 hours, then got better.  The next day around 1:00, I became ill again with flu-like symptoms and had to leave work.  Headache and body aches mostly.  I was ill with these symptoms for a 24 hour period. Ironically tracking back, I received my 2nd Dose of the Pfyzer Vaccine on January 6, 2021 at 8:45 a.m. and this occurred on February 13th at 2:15 a.m. I have not had any other issues before this nor any signs of damage to the nerve or ear that regularly affects Vertigo Patients per my Neuro and ENT. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Typical symptoms starting 3-12-21 at ~9pm of mildly elevated temperatures (~99.8 degrees F), body aches, headache. These continued for ~24 hours and I felt well from ~9pm on 3-13-21 until mid-afternoon on 3-14-21 started having mild intermittent upper abdominal pains. These continued until ~7pm that day when I started experiencing abdominal distention, cyclical abdominal cramping, nausea and frequent and deep belching. Around 9pm 3-14-21 experienced several episodes of small volume but urgent episodes of diarrhea but with sensation of needing to go more but couldn't.  Abdominal distention, cyclical abdominal cramping, nausea, and belching all increased throughout the evening/night until  around 2am had a episode of large vomiting. Continued to feel need to have diarrhea but no actual stools occurred throughout the night.  Continued through night to have belching, distention, cyclical abdominal cramping. 3-15-21 experienced significant fatigue, some continued abdominal cramping, abdominal distention increased again (after going down some after episode of vomiting), fever intermittently (up to ~101), nausea to point of not being able to eat anything, significant body aches and headache.  Weight dropped ~ 7lbs between am of 3-14 and 3-16. The evening of 3-15 I started to feel better, was able to keep down Tylenol, most symptoms improved, able to sleep that night. Have felt well other than fatigued and some mild uneasiness in stomach since waking up on 3-16.  Myself and husband are both physicians and we are concerned I experienced symptoms of partial small bowel obstruction evening of 3-14. I was going to seek ER evaluation evening of 3-15 but started feeling better

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within two hours of my shot, I had a headache/muscle aches and felt dizzy/dissociated, and left work early. I started to feel feverish in the early evening, I began experiencing nausea around 3 am that night. This became vomiting about twenty minutes later. I vomited four times over the course of the next half hour: 3:30-4:00 am. I also started experiencing diarrhea at about 4:00 am. I had five loose, near-water stools over the course of the rest of the night until around 9 am, two of which I vomited at the same time. By the time the worst of it stopped, I'd vomited 10 times from 3:30 am  - 10 am. I also experienced a fever from that afternoon onward, with chills/night sweats throughout the worst of the digestive upset until the morning. I couldn't keep fluids down until midmorning 3/18 and couldn't keep solids down until that evening, around 7 pm. It's 3/19 and I've had two glasses of water and a piece of toast and still feel nauseous. A friend of mine had some Zofran, which I took one dose of around 10 am 3/18, which allowed me to keep fluids down and not have to return to the hospital.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1/7/21: injection site started to turn red, swell, itch and was hot ~12 pm; by 7 pm redness had extended to apx. 3 in. wide by 2 in. high; also I had extreme pain in my back between my shoulder blades and had a hard time breathing. These symptoms persisted until 1/10/21; on 1/10/21 the redness turned from swollen and smooth to not swollen and bumpy - rash like. By 1/12/21 the swelling had gone away, but the rash had turned red and spread to more area on my arm. The rash reached its full size on 1/14/21 of apx. 6 in. wide by 4 in. high making a "box" like shape with a circle (apx. 2 in dia.)inside of the rash box; I was still having a hard time breathing; I saw the Dr. on 1/13/21 and was diagnosed with respirator infection. He prescribed antibiotics and prednisone. I felt better by 1/18/21, but then started having more back pain. Went back to the Dr. and was told I was having severe muscle spasms possibly due to the respiratory infection; was prescribed a muscle relaxer. The (1st ) doctor did not feel the symptoms I experienced were due to the vaccination, but all of the symptoms started as soon as my injection site started to have a reactions. I finally felt better without medication on 1/29/21. I received my second shot on 2/2/21 and had normal symptoms the day after (body aches, fever, chills, fatigue). Thank you! :)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: (Note: Difficult to read handwriting on lot number, could also be DOV 6208 or DOV 6Z08) I woke up around 12 hours after having the vaccine and felt a strange sensation in my head, almost like a helmet of fog over my head, sort of a numb feeling, and I noticed that also my eyes and lips felt numb. I ate a grapefruit as I usually do (not sectioned by myself). I felt extremely lethargic, had joint pain and a weakness. I usually have tea and toast in the morning and as I was at the table buttering my toast, I had an overwhelming nausea come on. I then woke up on the floor. My companion told me I went unconscious and slipped off the chair. Perhaps the whole episode was a maximum of 20 seconds. My first words were "Where am I?" and my companion told me. I rest on the floor, directed my companion to read on the internet about stroke and we ascertained I was okay, so I was thinking completely clearly. In any case, I had the fog in my head the entire day, and also today, but I feel a little better and was able to eat after 4 hours of rest. I wasn't able to fall asleep but I rested the entire day and slept a couple of hours during the night, which is not like me. I usually don't have any problem sleeping.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a 50 year old woman who presents 10 minutes post-vaccination of her first Moderna vaccine in the left deltoid.  She describes that 5 minutes following vaccination that she started to experience pain in the left arm, which was then followed by a burning sensation in her left upper back and mid sternum.  She denies a history of similar episodes.  She denies a history of reactions to vaccines received in the past.  She does describe sensitivities to the top 8 allergen foods, relating that she experiences abdominal bloating.  She also describes a sensitivity to codeine, specifically Tylenol #4, relating that she experiences itching of the skin.  She denies chest pain, headache, lightheadedness, dizziness, cramping abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, urticaria, pruritus, swelling of the lips, mouth, and tongue.  Past medical history of obesity.   During medical observation, while waiting for EMS to arrive onsite, the patient began to describe the feeling of something "being stuck in her throat," relating that it "felt odd to swallow" and that she was experiencing a metallic taste in her mouth.  Upon examination, no signs of swelling of the throat, lips, and tongue.  Neck was supple and without signs of edema.  Bilateral lungs were clear to auscultation in all fields.  No audible wheezing or stridor.  No visible use of accessory muscles.
Pain on left arm. Limited motion of left arm.
OTHER_MEDS: Allopurinol 100 mg Simvastatin 10 mg Centrum multivitamin  Vitamin B complex Vitamin C 1000 mg Calcium with Vit D Biotin  5000 mcg

Shingles; Information has been received from a lawyer regarding a case in litigation referring to a female patient (pt) of unknown age. Information about concurrent condition, medical history and concomitant medication was not reported. On or around 22-OCT-2015, the pt was vaccinated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) (strength, dose, lot#, expiration date and route unknown) for routine health maintenance and its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). Shortly after receiving the vaccine, the pt suffered varicella-like rash, redness, blisters, bumps and ongoing pain in her legs and buttocks and was diagnosed with shingles. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt's symptoms had resulted in physical limitations not presenting prior to using the product. The pt also experienced mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of her condition. As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of the product, the pt suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt had suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of the event was not recovered. The causality assessment was considered as related by the lawyer.  The lawyer considered the event shingles to be disability.

fever; aphasia/could not talk; This spontaneous report was received from a female patient of unknown age referring to herself. The patient's medical history included renal transplant. Her concomitant medications and drug reactions or allergies were not provided.  On an unspecified date in November 2011, the patient was vaccinated with either pneumococcal vaccine, polyvalent (23-valent) (PNEUMOVAX23) or pneumococcal 13v conj vaccine (crm197) (PREVNAR 13) (formulation, strength, dose, anatomical dose, route of administration, lot # and expiration date were not reported for both) as prophylaxis (the patient could not remember which). She reported that she developed a fever about 3-4 hours after receiving the vaccine and had to be taken to the emergency room by ambulance after the fever continued to rise. She was hospitalized for 2-3 nights and was not able to remember much from the hospitalization. She reports that when she woke up in the hospital she could not talk and experienced aphasia that the doctor said could have been results of the high fever. Unspecified treatment was given for the events. The outcome of the events was reported as recovered about 1 week later.  The relatedness between the suspect therapies and the events was not provided.

She finally got up and went into the bathroom and by 3:30 had coughed up little round, clear jellyfish.  Then she stopped coughing and went back to bed for 15 minutes, and then at 3:45 started getting diarrhea which she had until 10:30 AM.   She called Pfizer and reported her reaction and talked to them. During that time she had a lot of diarrhea and her body was starting to ache, joints and muscles.  She did not take her temperature and went back to bed, and slept until she could get up and go to the bathroom.  She then took her temperature and it was 100.7, which her normal is 97. 3.  She slept from 11:00 PM Wednesday until 11:00 AM Thursday.  She could not stay awake for long  before falling back to sleep.  Yesterday she did sleep most all of the day, and did not eat anything since Tuesday evening and did have a piece of toast yesterday.  Today, 3/19/21 she is able to get up, dressed and gotten downstairs to get something to eat and has lost 6# in this time period.  She is feeling wimpy, and her temp is down to 97.3, her pulse ox is 98%, pulse in the 70s.  She's achy, and has rubbed on Aspercreme  and has taken Tylenol a couple of times.  She is still very weak, probably dehydrated and going to get something to eat as she has just gotten up.  She is foggy thinking, but feels that once she rests, eats and gets strength she will be fine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Death; not able to stand up or walk; extreme weakness; he did not feel well; not able to stand up or walk; A spontaneous report was received from the patient's wife concerning a male (age not provided) who experienced extreme weakness/asthenia, did not feel well/malaise, unable to walk/gait inability, and unable to stand/dysstasia.  The patient's medical history included lung disease which required oxygen support. Per patient's wife, no concomitant products were in use within two weeks of the event. The patient's wife also stated he does not take any daily medications.  On 21 Jan 2021, prior to the onset of events, the patient received the first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 ( Batch number 029L20A) by injection into his left arm for prophylaxis of Covid-19 infection.  After receiving the vaccine, the patient's wife stated he did not feel well. He experienced extreme weakness. He was not able to stand up or walk for the first few days after getting the shot. "He could not walk even 3 steps and get in the car".   On 09 Feb 2021, the patient felt a little bit better and could walk from one bedroom to another. No Medications were used to treat the patient's symptoms. No relevant medical tests were provided.  The patient had an appointment with his healthcare provider (date and time not provided) and was told he could not get the second dose of vaccine unless he got better.    The patient's wife stated she is not blaming the vaccine because her husband had a lung disease prior to getting the vaccine.  His doctor said, (per his wife) this lung disease had weakened him to the point he could not drive his car anymore. His brain was fine before the vaccine.  On 03 Mar 2021, the patient's wife called to say that the patient had finally passed away on 13 Feb 2021.   The second dose of mRNA-1273 was withheld in response to the events while waiting for the patient's condition to improve however; it was never given due to the patient's death.  The events of did not feel well, extreme weakness, unable to walk, and unable to stand were not resolved (presumably) prior to the patient's death. The patient died on 13 Feb 2021. The cause of death was not provided. Plans for an autopsy were not provided.  Company Comment: The reported events, death, malaise, asthenia, gait inability, and dysstasia were considered possibly related to mRNA-1273.; Reporter's Comments: This is a case of  death in a male subject with a hx of lung disease requiring oxygen, who died 23 days after receiving first dose of vaccine. I had my 2nd shot in the evening of  Feb 13.  On Sunday in the mid afternoon around 2, I started experiencing chills and aches. I didn't feel like eating at all. I ate a little in the evening but I mainly slept the last half of the day. I took 2 Tylenol ever 4 hours and kept on that and took a Tylenol PM when I finally gave up and went to bed. Then next 3 days, throughout all these days, Mon - Wed, I had an excruciating headache and more joint pain especially in my ankles.  My headaches came from the back of my lower neck to my forehead. My entire shoulder was  sore the entire time.  I had a low grade fever only on Monday (Day 2). The injection site was red and warm to the touch the entire time. It was also very itchy and a tiny bit swollen and with a little bit of maybe a rash? I experienced chills on the first 2 days after my injection. Today is day 5 and I still continue to have gastric issues, not really wanting to eat even though I have been feeling hungry, a bit queasy throughout the 5 days. I drank peppermint tea through the past 5 days as it was the only thing that felt good in my body.  On Tuesday after too much stomach upsets, I chose to eat the BRATY and only ate bananas, yogurt, very finely chopped apples, and crackers. By Wed, I more hungry to tried to eat light and a not a lot. Today Friday, Day 5, I chose to eat some Soup and that seems OK. I still have a headache but not as severe as on Day 2 and 3. My injection site is starting to look normal.
HISTORY: I have a mild form of Psoriasis in my scalp and joints.
ALLERGIES: I have a mild form of Psoriasis in my scalp and joints. Many chemicals irritate my skin.

She was eventually transferred to another hospital on 3/12 at 1300.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Unable to think; wobbly legs; Weak legs; Unable to eat; Dizzy; Shortness of breath/ Difficulty breathing; Fever of 101 degrees Fahrenheit; Chills; Nauseated; A spontaneous report was received from a Health Care Professional concerning 69 years old female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced Mental impairment, which is medically significant and experienced Dyspnoea, Chills, Pyrexia, Muscular weakness, Mobility decreased, Nausea, Dizziness, Feeding disorder and Product dose omission issue of routine medicines.  The patient's medical history was provided as Covid-19 infection on OCT 2020 and current illness was provided as back problem and 11 mm gallstone.  Historical medication was reported as REMDESIVIR for Covid-19 infection.  Relevant concomitant medications were reported as Lisinopril-HCTZ daily, Mobic 15 mg daily, Tylenol 1000 mg as needed up to 3 times daily, Multivitamin, Vitamin C, Vitamin D, Vitamin B12, Calcium and Zinc.  On 05 MAR 2021, prior to the onset of the event, the patient received their first dose of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch: 024A21A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.   On 06 MAR 2021, the patient woke and felt like she was dying, described as having difficulty breathing and almost hyperventilating. She called her daughter-in-law who was a hospital nurse who advised her to breath slowly. The patient had shortness of breath, chills, and a temperature of 101 degrees Fahrenheit. Her legs were so weak that she had to use a walker to get from her bed to the couch, where she stayed until 2:30 am Sunday morning 7Mar2021. While she was on her couch she used a heating pad and was not able to sit up because she was nauseated and dizzy. She was unable to eat anything since Friday night until Sunday afternoon at 1:30 pm. She said she couldn't think on Saturday, and she missed her medicines until she was able to resume taking them Sunday evening 07 Mar 2021. The symptoms were not treated, except for use of the heating pad on Saturday.   On 07-mar-2021, Sunday morning at 2:30 am her fever broke. The patient was not as nauseated and did not get dizzy, so she sat up. The patient legs were not as weak and were not wobbling, so she went back to her bed. She began feeling better by 6 or 7 pm on Sunday evening, with no fever, chills, and walking fine.   On 08 Mar 2021 she feels fine, excepting she has still had some shortness of breath. The patient had status post Covid-19 infection since October 2020. The patient was hospitalized and received remdesivir therapy for Covid-19 infection prior to receiving the Moderna Covid-19 first dose. She also was already scheduled for two surgeries, one on her back and one for a 11 mm gallstone removal, prior to receiving this first vaccine dose. Her doctor told her she must have the Moderna Covid-19 vaccine prior to beingable to have her surgeries. She describes her symptoms as feeling like she had Covid-19 again.    Laboratory details were not provided. Treatment information was provided as heating pad.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown.  On 07 MAR 2021, the outcome of the event's Mental impairment, Chills, Pyrexia, Muscular weakness, Mobility decreased, Nausea, Dizziness,  feeding disorder and Product dose omission issue of routine medicine was considered as resolved.  At the of this report, the outcome of the event's Dyspnoea was considered as not resolved.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. SYMPTOM_TEXT: 0701.   Since starting the COVID-19 vaccine program, the has always used the doses before they approached the expiration date.  This time, there were 16 vials of the Pfizer vaccine that had not been used and set to expire. The labeled expiration date and time were clearly present on the outside of the bag containing the doses.  On the morning of 10 March 2021, a pharmacist retrieved 1 vial at 0754 and 7 vials at 1138 from that allocation and provided them to nursing for the day?s administrations.  The pharmacy placed those doses in a new amber bag and did not label the bag with an expiration date and time.   The nursing team received the vials, diluted and drew up 20 doses that were administered to patients before 1230.    The charge nurse did not question the expiration date until after 20 patients had been vaccinated.  At that time she messaged the pharmacist to verify the expiration date.  The pharmacist indicated that the label did not state am or pm and misinterpreted the expiration time for the doses as 7:01 PM rather than 7:01 AM.  There was not a defined double check at the time of distribution from the pharmacy to nursing  The remaining 11 vials were quarantined.  The pharmacy manager contacted the manufacturer.  According to Pfizer it?s recommended to use the thawed vaccine within 120 hours, but can be used up to 144 hours.  The doses in question were administered before 125 hours after they were thawed.  The remaining expired vials will be wasted and appropriate notifications sent.  Assessment: Twenty patients received Pfizer COVID vaccine 5 hours passed the labeled expiration date and time.  While exceeding the manufacturer's recommended beyond use dating, the doses were within the acceptable 144 hours post thaw period and still safe for patient administration.  There was misinterpretation of the labeled expiration time by the dispensing pharmacist, the container of COVID vaccine vials provided to nursing was not labeled with an expiration date or time, there was not a double check on hand off, the nursing team did not double check the expiration date/time before dilution or administration.  Recommendation:  When repackaging COVID Vaccine vials for distribution to vaccination centers, a label including the expiration date and time should be placed on the new container.  When COVID vaccine is transferred from one location or department to the next, a double check of the product, quantity, integrity and expiration date and time may prevent a recurrence of this situation.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: A week later, my left arm (a couple inches below the injection site) started itching and I developed a small red patch. It grew to a 3x3 inch path by Friday, the 15th. I increased my Zyrtec - taking an extra one each day. It was gone by Sunday, the 17th. It came back on the Wednesday the 20th - at the same spot. I don't think it went away. And then a week later, 1/28/2021 - I had breakthrough hives again - which can be anywhere on my body. Once my hives started - that spot just stayed - it's just there. (I have chronic hives). (My chronic hives  - stays in remission with meds). Other than that one Zyrtec, I had been off my hives medication and in remission from hives for an entire year. On the 29th of January, I had the IUD taken out. When my hives started on 28th, I added medications:  I increased to 40 mg Zyrtec; Pepsid - 40 in morning and 40 in night - in addition to all my other meds. I was prescribed Singulair - 10 mg in the morning. This did not resolve my hives. Hives actually got worse during the course of that week up until the second vaccine which was on February 4th. Telehealth visit - and I happened to have an annaul allergy doctor visit on January 25th  - who looked at it at that time.

This patient felt fine with the injection and for the 15 min following. He was dismissed to check out and make a follow up appt. While waiting in line to make his appt, he stated to his mother (who had given him a ride and stayed with him) that he felt faint. His mother shouted to staff nearby that he was going to pass out, so a staff person grabbed a chair for him. He sat in the chair, but did not fully lose consciousness. I ran to him with , told someone to get an ice pack, and asked his mother to sit in a chair next to him and place her hand on his right arm. I checked his bp at this time and it was 58/30. He was shaking all over, diaphoretic, pale,  and his muscles were weak.  He asked for water, so one was given to him, and he promptly drank the whole 16 oz bottle.  Over approximately 5 min, he came back to his normal LOC, stopped shaking and sweating, and stated that he was feeling better.  He was given a small bag of crackers and another bottle of water, which he quickly consumed before standing up. At this point, he stated that he was feeling hung over after staying out late the evening before drinking and celebrating St. Patrick's Day. Instructed him to make sure he is well hydrated before he comes for his second dose vaccination.

I was at home getting ready for bed when my arm felt a little funny so I looked at it and saw about 15 small bumps at and around the injection site. After about 1/2 hour they were getting bigger and had merged in to fewer larger bumps. I took a picture. about 2 hours later it had merged into 1 bump was hot and red. I called health because they were the ones who administered the vaccine. After speaking with the on-call nurse she recommended I see my primary care doctor with in 24 hours. The next morning the area was swollen about the size of a baseball , raised about 1/2 inch and hot as well as itchy. I was able to conduct a tele visit with my doctor and she said it looked infected and prescribed an antibiotic. When I got off work that evening I went and picked up the antibiotic and started them right away, by this time the swelling had grew to about a softball diameter. the next morning the swelling was greatly reduced and continued to shrink and disappear 3 days later. My skin had a strange texture to it in the area for about a month and a half.
PRIOR_VAX: soreness with slight red and swelling of injection site usually gone with in a day or two

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I experienced a missed miscarriage. I was pregnant during both doses of the vaccine (1st dose 1/15/21), but 2/12/21 (the day of the 2nd dose) was the day the gestational sac stopped growing. I was 8 weeks pregnant at this point. The ultrasound was on 2/17/21 and it was reported that I was supposed to be 8wk 6days, but gestational sac was only 8wk 1day. I was due on 9/23/21.   My PCP encouraged me to get the vaccine, knowing that I was pregnant. So I did.   Upon receiving my 2nd dose of the vaccine, I did not experience any symptoms and believe that my body was focused more on the vaccine than the development of the baby. Obviously I'm not positive that this was the cause, but I wanted to make it known, so I can hopefully prevent this from happening again, if the vaccine was indeed a contributor.
OTHER_MEDS: Prenatal Vitamin Folic Acid Vitamin D

LAB_DATA: FINAL DIAGNOSIS: A: Small intestine, duodenum, biopsy: Moderately active duodenitis with crypt apoptosis and partial villous blunting (see Comment). Immunostains for CMV, HSV-1/2, and VZV are negative. B: Stomach, body, biopsy: Gastric corpus mucosa with chronic inactive gastritis, intraepithelial lymphocytosis, and mildly thickened subepithelial collagen (see Comment). There is no intestinal metaplasia. An immunostain for Helicobacter is negative. C: Colon, random, biopsy: Mildly inflamed colonic mucosa with expanded lamina propria, intraepithelial lymphocytosis, and mildly thickened subepithelial collagen, highlighted by a trichrome stain (see Comment). COMMENT: There is active inflammation and injury involving both the upper and lower gastrointestinal tract. The overall pattern of injury is unusual, however, with lymphocytic/mild collagenous gastritis and colitis-like injury in the stomach and colon, respectively, and active duodenitis with neutrophilic infiltrate and associated partial villous blunting in the duodenum in the absence of significant intraepithelial lymphocytes or expanded subepithelial collagen. There is no chronic inflammatory alteration, and no granuloma is observed. No definite viral cytopathic change is identified. No Helicobacter organism is present. A unifying etiology includes a differential that encompasses drug, particularly in a patient with a clinical history of PD-1 inhibitor therapy such as nivolumab, as well as other possibilities such as infection, autoimmune disorder, and early IBD. Correlation with clinical, laboratory, and endoscopic findings is suggested. An additional immunostain for adenovirus is currently being performed at an outside institution, the results of which will be reported in an addendum.
CUR_ILL: 2 months prior to vaccination was on immunotherapy for treatment of melanoma

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient participated in a mass vaccine event with the local school system administered by local pharmacy.  After the vaccine was administered the patient was instructed to wait 30 minutes so she could be observed by a school nurse.  She said she noticed her lips were beginning to feel numb and looked in the mirror and noticed her face was beginning to turn red.  The nurse came over to assess the patient when she noticed the patient was developing hives on her face and neck and her eyes were becoming swollen.  The fire department with a paramedic unit was on site and came over to assess the patient.  They did not administer any medications as their protocol did not call for medications if the patient was not having difficulty breathing.  In the meantime 911 had been called and an ambulance arrived on site.  The patient refused transport and the ambulance left the site.  The nurse, pharmacist, and school staff would not allow the patient to leave the site until further evaluation for approximately 30 more minutes.  The nurse and pharmacist insisted the patient receive 50mg of diphenhydramine orally, and she agreed to comply.  The patient's friend was on site and agreed to drive the patient home and stay with her for at least four more hours.  The friend was instructed to call 911 if any of the symptoms worsened.  The patient was provided with an additional 2 x 25mg diphenhydramine capsules to take in  case needed.   The nurse called the patient at 1pm, and the patient indicated her symptoms were resolving.  The nurse called the patient again at 3pm, and the patient indicated she felt much better. The pharmacist called the patient on 03/15/21 at 4:45pm for additional follow-up.  The patient indicated she felt "wiped out" all day on 03/13/21 but felt much better by 03/14/21.  The pharmacist instructed the patient that even though she did not have an anaphylactic reaction she should NOT take the second dose of the Moderna vaccine, and that she should not receive the Pfizer vaccine either.
OTHER_MEDS: Vyvanse daily Claritin alternating with Zyrtec daily Larin BCP's Flintstone vitamin daily Protein powder with collagen daily Albuterol Inhaler as needed for exercise induced asthma Epi-Pen as needed for allergies to tree nuts

She was able to walk to the ambulance and was taken to Hospital with her husband.  She went to the emergency room at hospital to be evaluated . I followed up with the patient that afternoon at 4:00 PM and she was home. She was treated with IV Benadryl  per the patient in my follow up discussion with her and she also received a dose of oral prednisone taper along with oral Benadryl liquid to take at home. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Night following shot, I slept badly and felt cold all night.  When I wanted to get up to go to the bathroom around 5:30 AM, I could not get myself off and out of the bed.  It was like my legs wouldn't work. When I was finally up, I had no control of my bladder and urinated all the way into my bathroom. When I was done on the toilet, I started to stand up and lost my balance. I tried to reach for the door jam but missed and fell backwards onto the toilet and sat hard and hit my back very hard against the top of the toilet.  I helped back to bed by boyfriend but had to get up several more times that morning and had the same weakness in my legs and no control over my bladder. My boyfriend had to leave to go home, so I called my sister to come and stay with me in case I couldn't get up again. One she was here, I ate a small amount of roast chicken and slept most of the afternoon. I slept thru the night and felt stronger the next day. I felt very tired and sleepy for the next couple of days, but (3 days later) am now feeling and moving in a more normal manner.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a very pleasant 85-year-old male who presented to the emergency department first on 3/8/2021 via private vehicle accompanied by his spouse in no acute distress with complaints of left arm pain and swelling after receiving his Pfizer COVID vaccination on 3/2/2021.  Medical history includes hypertension, heart failure, CAD, GERD, diaphragmatic hernia, chronic left shoulder pain, among others. Patient states he received his vaccine on Tuesday and began to develop pain, swelling, and bruising at the injection site on Thursday. Since that time all of his symptoms have worsened. 9/10 pain this morning has lowered to a 4/10 after 2 tylenol, which he took approximately one hour prior to arrival. Is not anticoagulated but takes baby aspirin daily. He did stop this when he first noticed the bruising. Denies recent trauma, including falls. His chronic left shoulder pain is unchanged from baseline; the pain he presents to the ED for is located lower at the injection site. Further notes pain patches helpful with his pain.  Seen again on 3/15/2021 for persistence and involvement of his forearm with the bruising and pain.Over the last week the purple discoloration has migrated down his arm towards his hand.  He denies any new numbness or weakness in the arm. Exam reveals impressive and extensive ecchymosis that involves both his upper and lower arm and is circumferential in nature. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Received vaccine at approximately 12:30 pm  on 3/15/21 at 13 weeks pregnant (due date of 9/15/21). Weight and height 5'0", approximates 136lbs.   During injection there was a pain from the needle insert and immediate soreness. I would describe it as more painful than the flu shot that I received in November of 2021. I was then escorted to a chair for a 15 minute observation period. I did not have any allergic reactions to the shot. I continued to feel slight soreness in my left arm for the rest of the day.  At approximately 8 pm I began to feel "aches and pains" similar to those during a cold and flu. I took (1) regular strength Tylenol Acetaminophen 325 mg tablet. I began to feel a little bit warm around 9-10 pm and checked my temperature with an infrared thermometer and it was slightly elevated by a degree (no exact measurement). I  went to bed at approximately 11:30 pm.   At approximately 12:45 am I woke up and took my temperature. I first used the infrared thermometer and it came back as 99.4 F. I felt very warm so I then switched to an Oral thermometer for accuracy and began to record the following: 101.1 F - 12:45am (was under blankets so got out of bed to cool off) / 100.0 F - 1:05 am / 100.9 F - 1:20 am  At 1:10am I used a cold compress (small ice pack wrapped in a kitchen towel) to cool off and then took a luke-warm shower at 1:15 am (did not wet hair). I also drank a big water bottle of water (Tap Water) probably around 500ml. The room temperature was around 74 F. I re-measured my temp at 1:40 am and it decreased to 99.3 F. I took a 2nd Tylenol tablet (same as above) at 2 am. My temperature at 2:05 am was 100.0 F.  I then went in and out of sleep and recorded my temps every time I woke up and went to the bathroom / drank more water. 98.5 F at 3:55 am / 98.4 F at 5:55 am / 99.0 at 7:25 am. At 7:30am I took a 3rd & 4th Tylenol. Temp at 7:55am was 99.4F. I went back to sleep and then woke up at 9am to login remotely for work. Temp at 9:25 am was 98.7.  I then took a nap from 9:30 am to 12:00 pm (my boss told me to go to sleep after our call) and slept very soundly. When I woke up I felt a lot better. Aches and pains were no longer present and fever appeared to be gone. The worst of the symptoms were over. I then spot checked my temp a few times throughout the day: 98.0F at 12:15pm / 98.3 F at 1:40pm / 98.7 at 2:05 pm. At 2:15 pm I took a 5th Tylenol just in case. I took my last official temp at 2:20pm at 98.3 F.   At about 3pm 3/16 I had a telehealth visit with my OBGYN. She said that my symptoms were normal and everything looked ok. My test results from my 12 week sonogram I had 2 weeks prior were all OK as well. To my knowledge the baby is tracking healthy. Note that during the whole time I did not experience any symptoms related to the baby. No cramps or pains in my abdomen. I am happy to share any past or future data about my pregnancy if anyone reading this is interested in contacting me.  I then randomly measured my temp until bed but it never came back as higher than normal (didn?t write it down). Slept through the next night normal and woke up normal temp as well. I would say I was more tired than usual on 3/17 but did not have any more flu like symptoms. The only thing that remained was a soreness at the injection site. It was at the spot of injection and also kind of the general area. The pain/feeling completely went away by the end of the week 3/19.   This is a very long description of symptoms. I don?t know if it?s helpful or if anyone even read all of it. But I?m just writing it down for record.
OTHER_MEDS: (1) Prenatal Vitamin Tablet taken orally  (2) Meta Mucil 3-in-1 Fiber Psyllium Fiber Supplement taken orally
ALLERGIES: lactose intolerant no other known allergies to medications, food or other

On 05-Mar-2021, the patient developed a non-serious diarrhea (diarrhoea), rash on chest, rash worsened to her right hand and legs (rash), fever of 103 fahrenheit (pyrexia) and appetite loss (decreased appetite) two days following the administration of DIPHTHERIA-2/TETANUS/5 AC PERTUSSIS VACCINE. 1022 - Patient received her 1st Pfizer vaccine by RN.  She noted a history of vasovagal syncope to needles in the past (did not seem like it was complete syncope to all needle sticks per RN).  RN offered for her to lie down, but she said she felt ok sitting.  She did not endorse any history of severe allergies or reactions to injectables in the past; she was asked the necessary questions prior to vaccination.  We later learned she has Crohn?s and is on immunosuppressant Imuran for this disorder.  1023ish ? walked to checkout area  1025 - While sitting at the checkout registering for her second shot she started to feel faint and checkout staff called for help  1026 - RNs were getting the BP cuff on her. She appeared obtunded and slouching in her chair- eyes closed. Gentle sternal rub and she was able to open her eyes and tell us what her name was and ask to call her dad. BP 90/58. Cold cloths placed on her neck. Continuous pulse ox monitor placed, showing 99%.  1030 - Still drowsy and diaphoretic. Able to tell us that "she passes out when she gets shots" C/O nausea and vomited. Still in and out of awareness. NP is site coordinator is now present and suggests taking patient by wheelchair to safer and more private area for evaluation in SR Room.  Patient able to stand and transfer to wheelchair, which we did slowly and carefully.  1034 ? Now in safer and more private area SR room with NP and RN and Dr. Firemen are here and assessing the scene with medic assessing patient. Ambulance in route, about 5 - 10 minutes out per radio communication.  Checking BP every 2  minutes.  Now is 68/44. C/O nausea and vomited. Pulse ox won?t pick up.  Patient with decreasing LOC, eyes rolling back in head, unable to maintain posture seated, and not able to describe symptoms to us (unknown if she felt itchy but no obvious cutaneous manifestations).  Unable to visualize oropharynx.  1037- BP 57/40. NP administered Epi pen 0.3 mg dose to L lateral thigh due to s/s of systemic allergic reaction/anaphylaxis including 3 known body systems: hypotension (cardiovascular), vomiting (GI), and decreased LOC (neuro). No IV fluids immediately available but were preparing to obtain.  Staff getting cot for patient to lie down.  Provider spoke with her mom on the phone and informed her of event. Mom confirmed that she has often before passed out with vaccines and blood draws. Dad was on his way to center and rerouted to ER.  1038 - BP 68/45 Talking to medics and able to tell them she ate breakfast and that she has a hx of Crohn's and takes a monthly injection. Informed provider that her dad was on his way. EMS team here to transport to ER.  We were preparing to put her on a cot so help with her blood pressure/blood flow when she started to stabilize and EMS arrived with stretcher.    1040 - BP 97/53.  Patient is now alert and talking to us.  Says she has had syncope in the past ?but never anything like this.?    1041 - BP 115/53. Patient still alert and talking.  Oriented x 3.  1042 - Transported to ER by EMS ambulance on stretcher.  DEBRIEF: Somewhat atypical (no obvious cutaneous manifestations) and rapid, severe reaction.  Ddx vasovagal vs anaphylaxis.  Response to epi consistent with anaphylaxis reversal.  Perhaps immunosuppressant medication contributed to severity and rapidity of reaction.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I am a registered nurse. I also am very sensitive to joint pain and muscle pain due to my lupus so I was not surprised by my ?overreaction to the soreness of both injections. However: although I was one of the people who had a severe reaction to the injection in terms of the arm pain, I also experienced a lot of nerve pain down the arm injected into my hand and fingers from the swelling. I also had a large lump with redness and heat. It was more severe with dose number two. I also had pain into my left shoulder and neck. This didn?t concern me and I expected it. I also had severe joint pain bilaterally in all of my joints with malaise and fatigue. This also didn?t concern me. However in February after my second  Moderna vaccine, I began to experience shooting pain in my left back and chest ? just under my left shoulder blade and sometimes running around into my sternum area ?only when lying in the supine position (flat on my back) and only beginning a few minutes after lying down upon taking in a deep breath.  This pain was relieved by sitting up. Initially I thought I had a rib out of place and went to a chiropractor to have an adjustment. After a few visits to the chiropractor and some  Ice / massage, I still have this pain, now on both sides with shortness of breath. I feel it is connected to the vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: With the first vaccine I had a strong hypoglycemic episode 30 hours after the injection.  The next day, about 24 hrs. later I became very dizzy but didn't develop shaking, diaphoresis, or black spots in my vision.  (I've had hypoglycemic episodes rarely, maybe every several years, but I know well what they feel like.  No further episodes since then.  I wasn't prepared for the episode and didn't have candy or orange juice handy.  It required I lay down for 10 minutes while I was very shaky and cold, clammy diaphoresis.  Pita Chips helped---I presume.    Yesterday I received the second dose and 29 hours later I started getting hypoglycemic again but quickly drank some concentrated sugary lime juice.  I remained slightly shaken but never developed black spots or diaphoresis.  I still felt too light and shaky so I had another half glass of juice and feel normal after about 10 minutes.   When I reported this, my daughter, who is an ER doctor, was doubtful the first time it was vaccine related because of the 30 hour gap.  Before receiving the second dose, the doctor there also didn't believe it was related for the same reason.  But I find it very odd now that after both vaccines, at around the 30 hour mark, I had the same effects.  Except for a slight migraine- like headache, no other real symptoms----maybe some lethargy.  I'm not diabetic, so I'm not on insulin or diabetic pills.  I take a lower dose of blood pressure meds and have well-controlled hypertension.  I can't even remember the last time (in years) I had hypoglycemia, but I've never had it as bad as I did the first time.  Since I caught it this time with the juice and stopped the symptoms, I don't know if it would have reached the level of the first dose of vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: At 13:45 pt notified COVID-19 drive-thru vaccine station patient monitor that she was having facial flushing. Dr. and RN responded to patient in parking lot to assess. Patient reported that she had a reaction after her first dose of vaccine, she "felt it in her body," and lightheaded, and it took 3 hours for it to feel better. She also said that when clinical staff assessed her last time, she did not take her mask off, so they didn't know that her face was flushed and swollen. She said that she had talked to her PCP who recommended that she bring Benadryl to take after the vaccine if she had the same reaction. Pt states that while in line for vaccine, someone told her she should take the Benadryl before the vaccination, so she took 50mg.    VS:  BP 128/82, HR 56, RR 20, SpO2 98%. Heart sounds regular, lungs clear to auscultation. Pt denies nausea. No rash visible. Clinical staff stayed with patient. Pt also said that she had history of anaphylaxis to eggs. At 15 minutes, symptoms not progressing, but also not lessening. At 14:12, because patient had taken Benadryl and staff was unable to tell if allergic symptoms were lessened by the Benadryl, they contacted EMS to come assess the patient. EMS arrived at 14:20, report was given. EMS assessed pt in ambulance. AT 14:44, EMS released pt to home. She reported that she felt better and thanked clinical staff.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 8 days after first dose of Moderna vaccine, developed two red spots on upper left arm slightly below injection site. They were hot and red and tender to the touch. Flesh also felt somewhat hard/firm in that area. It hurt to move my arm. Took photo in the morning, and two hours later the spots had almost doubled in size, coming together as one larger red area that eventually covered most of my upper, outer arm. By the end of the day, the red area was approximately 7 inches long by 4 inches wide.  For context, on the day of the vaccine, I had heaviness and some discomfort in my arm (same as I experienced with the flu shot this year), but no redness. All discomfort disappeared in less than 2 days. Was very surprised to have an issue 8 days later.
LAB_DATA: Saw a healthcare provider mid-afternoon, who consulted with her dermatology colleague. No tests were run. They told me they have now seen 6 or 7 cases of this type of adverse reaction occurring 7-8 days after injection. Recommended ice, OTC pain killers and/or antihistamine. Said it should resolve on it's own.
OTHER_MEDS: amlodopine (5MG) , cod liver oil, women's multivitam, vitamin D, iron supplement, probiotic
ALLERGIES: penicillin, sulfates, two previous blood pressure medications

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Received 2nd Pfizer shot 2/25/2021.  To stave off side effects, I took 2 Ibuprofen before bed. In the morning, I was more wobbly than usual, but could make it to the bathroom and return to bed. A couple of hours later I had chills, bladder was not functioning well. I could not walk or stand and, could barely maneuver in bed. Went to hospital by ambulance, where I was given 125 MG of IV Solumedrol intravenously. Less than an hour later, I could walk and leave the hospital using my quad cane and the arm of a loved one. I continued to improve and am currently at the condition I was in before the 2nd vaccine injection . Walking was impaired after the first injection two weeks prior, but I was not forced to call an ambulance for help.
LAB_DATA: The staff at hospital measured my vital signs, tested my urine and checked my blood sugar.
PRIOR_VAX: Described earlier.

On Thursday, March 18, 2021 client  received his first dose of Pfizer COVID vaccine (LOT # ER2613, EXP 7/2021) at approximately 2:45pm by vaccinator. During assessment of screening questions, client stated he has a history of anxiety when getting vaccinations. After vaccine was administered, client stated he "felt anxious and dizzy." Vaccinator took his pulse at this time: 88bpm. Client was given water and sat at vaccination table for approximately 15 minutes. At 3:00pm, client walked with a steady gait to the Observation Area and EMT performed the following vitals assessment: At 3:05pm, vitals: BP: 130/p, HR: 60, RR: 13, Skin: dry, pink, warm. Vitals at 3:10pm: BP: 128/p, HR: 58, RR: 13, skin: dry, pink, warm. Vitals at 3:15pm: BP: 132/p, HR: 60, RR: 14, skin: dry, pink, warm. (p= over palpation-cuff too small for client). Client was observed watching videos on his phone and stated to EMT his anxiety had significantly lowered. No further interventions indicated. Client was educated by Lead RN & EMT on signs and symptoms of adverse reactions and when to go to the ED/call MD. Client left vaccination site with a steady gait and was driven home by his mother.

At this point I am going to give you an account of my past 14 months health and how I know it is related to the covid virus.   i am sure i have had long covid  from december 2019 or january 2020 to the present based on symptoms i incurred on these dates. On my first night I ended up vomiting my guts out at 2:00 in the am. The following 2 weeks I had constant diarrhea.  At the end of those 2 weeks,  i ended up in emergency room. And this all happening when  i haven't' vomited in over 30 years.  vital signs and blood work were good at the hospital and the drs were confused as to why i felt so bad. i returned home the next day where our permanent home is,  and 3 months later the covid thing surfaced. at first being thought of as a respiratory disease. then in the past months it is surfacing that it may now be considered a gastrointestinal disease that progresses to a respiratory disease. after checking the five main symptoms of long covid i discovered that i have at least 3 of the 5  common symptoms for this. Those being extreme fatigue, joint pain, and cough. In addition to the long covid symptoms, I have encountered tasting issues on and off again.  I have had many discussions with my primary care doctor, and no results or conclusive information came from my inquiries. Then on feb 12, 2021 I got my first moderna shot. About 2-3 weeks later I encountered a sharp pain in a muscle in my neck left side. Shortly thereafter I got very light headed. Then another  week later while  driving a motor home, I encountered a frightening experience with my eyes, and the neck pain and soreness was still there. My vision was very blurred and I was seeing double vision at different angles. I ended up at the medical center and was admitted for 4 days. Before I was admitted, I saw a local ophthalmologist here and he diagnosed me with a condition known as ?edema in optic nerve, inferior, consistent with optic nephropathy?. The symptom I had to get me to the doctor was I was losing eyesight in my left eye. After hd steroid treatment for 4 days, and a plethora of tests, including spinal tap, multiple mri?s, and probably over 20 blood tests (11 at one draw), I was released 3-18-2021 and still can?t see above the equator line of my left eye. And I also am extremely sensitive to light. I also have sensitivity inside my eye as best described as a soreness, especially when I try to look upwards. I have a follow up appt with the ophthalmologists that I first saw that advised me to get to the hospital. And that is on mar 26th 2021.  to mention another point of interest, my granddaughters boyfriends mother is a charge nurse at the emergency ward at the hospital, and she has said that they also have recently encountered emergency patients, who have recently received moderna, and are also having issues with eye problems. What problems in particular, I haven?t a clue at this time.  This is at the very least, extremely alarming to me, and I have no idea whether I may completely lose all function of my left eye., or not. But I adamantly feel this should be investigated by the cdc and any and all other agencies that should be involved.  I would be willing to have further discussions via phone or whatever to help you out with an investigation.
