SYMPTOM_TEXT: I started experiencing flu-like symptoms at around 5 PM on 3/14/21.  I was feverish and had chills, muscle aches, and a headache.  I had very strong chills for a few hours and then I noticed that my resting heart rate was around 128 bpm at around 1:30 AM on 3/15/21.  I was running a 100.6 fever at that time.  My fever subsided in the morning and the headache persisted throughout the day, and I was very tired as I did not get much sleep the night before.  I did not work that day (Monday, 3/15).  At the time I was about 7 weeks pregnant.  I noticed some very light spotting later in the day on 3/15, and then I continued spotting on 3/16.  I consulted a midwife at the  facility at 4 PM on 3/16/21 and took a blood test to measure my hCG hormone levels.  The following day, 3/17, I received the results that I had a normal level of hCG hormone and normal hemoglobin levels.  As the day continued, the spotting turned into bleeding, and eventually the bleeding became heavy starting around 4 PM.  I received an ultrasound on 3/18/21 at 8 AM and later spoke with a midwife from facility at 11 AM that day, confirming that there was no viable pregnancy detected via ultrasound.  I had lost quite a bit of blood at that point.  I am, as of 8:35 PM on Friday,  March 19th, still bleeding and experiencing the impact of miscarriage.
LAB_DATA: Blood test to determine hCG hormone levels conducted at facility, 3/16/21 at 4 PM Transvaginal ultrasound conducted at facility, 3/18/21 at 8 AM
OTHER_MEDS: Megafood Baby & Me 2 Prenatal multivitamin, Nordic Naturals Prenatal DHA Supplement, NatureMade Vitamin D3 supplement

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 30 hours after 1st Moderna dose on  02/16/2021 I got a red, itchy rash a few inches from injection site on my upper arm.  It lasted less than an hour.  Following 2nd dose of Moderna on 03/16/2021,  I woke up two days later (03/18/2021) with a much larger, more painful rash (several large red welts) a few inches from the injection site.  Onset was overnight while sleeping, so estimated time is 36-40 hours after vaccination.  It's now the evening of 03/19/2021,  about 68 hours post-injection.  The rash is still there, still itchy and slightly painful, beginning to fade - is now pink rather than red.   I'm hoping it will resolve in a few more days.  I assume this is a subcutaneous allergic reaction that some people get with Moderna.  I'm reporting this because I read some articles that said these reactions  after second doses were milder or nonexistent in people who got the reaction  after first doses.  My case is the exact opposite, with the second dose reaction being much stronger.
HISTORY: Osteoporosis Mild form of lupus  (not currently taking any drugs for this, with my rheumatologist's agreement)
ALLERGIES: Penicillin and some other antibiotics Tramadol  Seasonal allergies (tree pollen)

We had a vaccine reaction today at pharmacy 1870. Patient signed up vaccine online.   I saw on her form that she had a reaction to vaccine. , and discussed the vaccine reaction with her.  She said she had hives to influenza vaccine five years ago, but had influenza vaccines every year since including 2020 without incident.        I gave her the vaccine (Janssen) and almost immediately she said she felt tingling in her arm.  I had her sit in site of my gatekeeper for the vaccines.  In less than 5 minutes, she was swelling and red in the arm and it crossed over to her chest neck and the other arm.  She asked for a benadryl tablet and we complied, but the swelling continued to get worse. We immediately called 911 and the paramedics arrived in about 5 minutes. They gave her iv benadryl and transported her to hospital for observation.  Employee followed up with patient this afternoon.  She had been released from hospital and is doing well.  She was very pleased that we called to ask about her well-being.
PRIOR_VAX: hive influenza 5 years previous

6 hours after 2nd dose of vaccine I could feel my body starting to react.  Aches and pains increased as the time went on.  I went to bed and around 12 hours after the injection I got a headache that was unbearable.  It felt like someone was hitting my head with an ax. The pain was  excruciating.  I went through the night with the pain feeling like my head would explode.  In the morning I was totally exhausted and my body hurt all over.  I took Tylenol and went back to bed.  Put warm cloths on my head and face.  My sinus hurt, my teeth hurt. my throat hurt. my eyes hurt.  Awful!!! Spent the entire day in bed.  I continued taking Tylenol every 6 hours.  It did help a little.  By Friday I was seeming to feel a little better.  Still have mild headache and body aches and stomach upsets; but better than the first 24-36 hours.  Hoping to continue to improve each day.  Never expected any side effects as severe.  Most people said sore arm and feeling tired.  I do hope the worse is over.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: a 71 year old female presented to clinic for the first of 2 c-19 vaccines. She verbalized nervousness. She stated she felt well today; afebrile, denies n/v/d, malaise or fatigue.  No known sick contacts. Daughter with her. Much discussion about which arm to vaccinate and how it will affect her ability to watch TV tonight [staying with mom to be watched for any vaccine reaction. Mom is 96].  I admin Moderna covid vaccine into left delt  at 7:40 and continued chatting with patient/ daughter.  Daughter going to drive mom to the grandmother's house for the evening, has left her own car somewhere.  PT asked if she has to go to the waiting room to wait or if she could just wait in exam room? I reminded her several others waiting and she is suppose to wait out there. She stated she didn't think she could make it, starts to slide sideways in her seat.  Never losing consciousness, never falling to floor, her head lolled back and her speech began to slur.  I put her feet up in second chair and pulled her arms into her lap. Called to reception for help, had her call 911 and obtain E kit.  PT was still speaking/ rambling. + pallor, weakness.  Obtained VS at 7:47pm [WNL: 118/74, 69, 18 97% on RA].  Color began to improve without any intervention. by the time EMS arrived, PT was able to stand and to speak clearly. She declined to go to hospital for further evaluation.
CUR_ILL: NONE TO MY KNOWLEDGE; STATED SHE FELT WELL PRIOR

Assisted stretching manuvers did not elicit/exacerbate/alleviate parestheisa Psych: appropriate, thoughts linear and non-tangential A/P: 66 yo Veteran at vaccination clinic for 1st dose of Moderna, who experienced post vaccination adverse effect. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Reason for Appointment  1. INFECTION IN ARM AFTER VACCINE  History of Present Illness  General:  Pt initiated and verbally consents to phone visit, pt without capability of televisit in lieu of clinic visit to limit exposure/contact during COVID19 pandemic. The pt and myself are present for today's visit.  68 y/o male presents today with c/o arm infection after vaccination. Pt had his second Moderna COVID-19 vaccine on 03/11/2021. He noted a sore arm after vaccinatino, but had no serious reactions or side effets immediately following vaccination. 2 days after vaccination, he noticed a small streak of blood from his injection site on his pillow. He covered the area with a bandaid. When later removing the bandaid, he noticed the area was red and there was some clear fluid on the bandaid. He cleaned the area with some peroxide and used some antibiotic ointment on it. The next day he noticed that in addition to the area being red, there was now an area of white pus approximately the size of a dime at the injection site. Pt notes that he called the Health Department to report the issue, they told him to contact his PCP which is why this appointment was scheduled. Pt did request an in-person appointment, but was told that he would have to schedule a phone visit with me. Today, the pt reports that there is still an area of pus about the size of a dime at the injection site. The surrounding area of redness is reducing. He notes that the pain in his arm also seems improved today. Pt denies fever, chills, lightheadedness/dizziness, N/ V, palpitations.  Vital Signs  WI 188, Ht 5 ft 6 in, BMI 30.34 Index, Ht-cm 167.64 cm, Wt-kg 85.28 kg.  Examination  General Examination:  GENERAL APPEARANCE: alert, in no distress.  LUNGS: Speaks in full sentences, no respiratory distress, no audible stridor or wheezing.  NEUROLOGIC: alert and oriented.  PSYCH: alert, oriented x4, cognitive function intact, speech clear.  Assessments  1. Adverse effect of other vaccines and biological substances, initial encounter - (Primary)  2. Infection following immunization, initial encounter - Treatment  I. Adverse effect of other vaccines and biological substances, initial encounter  Notes: From pt's history, this sounds like a mild superficial skin infection. Pt may benefit form I&D. I attempted to schedule the pt with a provider in our office today, but there is no availablility. He has been advised to go tot an urgent care or to the ER for treatment. Pt is to f/u with me next week. I will be requesting that my staff file a VAERS for this patient.  2. Others  Notes: 30 minutes spent on this phone visit.  Follow Up  1 Week (Reason: Injection site infection)

Patient received the vaccine on 3/6/2021. She was found unresponsive at home with fixed gaze to the right on 3/8/2021. Taken to Medical CTR where initial evaluation CVA but STAT MRI -> encephalitis. Transported to another hospital. Pt had encephalitis with possible seizure. I am not sure this is a vaccine related event but I am reporting it.    Patient is a 77 y.o. female with a past medical history of prediabetes, hypertension, HLD, depression, arthritis, fibromyalgia who presents with altered mental status and encephalopathy with likely seizure.   Patient lives with granddaughter and daughter however patient is independent at home.   On 3/8, Patient developed new onset altered mental status associated with "staring off" and not responding to the family as per granddaughter. EMS was called and patient was taken to outside hospital where there was initial concern for stroke. CT head as well as CT angiogram were completed, which did not show significant stenosis. With unclear aspects of exam patient underwent MRI brain without contrast showing flair changes in the parieto-occipital area of the left hemisphere along with the temporal lobe as well as faint restricted diffusion in the same area. In the emergency department at the outside hospital, she was noted to have fixed gaze to the right as well as significant difficulty following commands. She was given Ativan as well as Keppra 1.2 g. Patient was started on vancomycin, ampicillin, acyclovir, doxycycline, as well as dose of dexamethasone. Patient was then transferred to hospital.   Encephalopathy w/ likely seizure event: As per granddaughter patient was at her baseline throughout the weekend and as of 3/8/2021 patient with altered mental status staring off and not responsive to family members along with notable aphasia. Outside hospital completed CT head as well as CT angiogram with no large vessel occlusion. MRI without contrast was completed showing flair changes of the left parieto-occipital lobe as well as the left temporal lobe with mild DWI changes, Initially there was concern for encephalitis with seizures, and patient was provided Ativan, Keppra 1.5 g, ampicillin, vancomycin, doxycycline, acyclovir as well as a dose of dexamethasone. Patient also present with slight fever to 100.2. Of note patient did received a dose of dexamethasone. Patient also presented with slight fever to 100.2. Of note patient did  received first COVID vaccine on Saturday, 3/6/2021. LP notable for elevated WBC (17 in tube 1), neutrophilic predominance, protein 101, glucose 92. Repeat MRI/MRA head the following day showed improving T2 hyperintensities in the left posterior hemisphere, favoring post-ictal changes given improvement but encephalitis cannot be ruled out based on the available data. During her hospitalization, patient was treated with acyclovir (Stopped when HSN was negative) as well as ampicillin, cefepime, and vancomycin (stopped clinical Improvement and LP results). Patient received Keppra 500 mg tice daily throughout her stay. Continuous video EEG for this first two days of her stay revealed LRDA but no seizures. Patient continued to improve throughout her stay and was deemed stable for discharge to home without outpatient therapy on 3/12. She was discharged on Keppra 500mg twice daily and referred to clinic for follow up.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: March 12, 2021 - On Friday about 2pm, I started with a runny nose ? by Sunday afternoon it was like a faucet turned on ? running down my face. March 13 - Saturday morning, I started coughing c chest congestion, and had Phlegm rattling in my chest, started sneezing very frequently/ some diarrhea.  Otherwise, I felt fine. March 14 - Sunday morning, I started wheezing slightly, coughing more and sneezing frequently.  Felt fine.  Went shopping.  Nose ran so much in store, had to run to the store to get paper towels to catch it.  Later, when I carried a heavy bag of groceries from one car 12 feet to another, noticed I was very exhausted and had to rest about 15 minutes before driving home.  Wheezing more. Monday, March 15, I took my B/P meds at 1:00am and my blood pressure was way up x 4 (160?s/ 70?s) p58-64,  at 2:08am ? B/P was 183/92) so I took my PRN Clonidine and ate all the high Potassium foods I had in the house.   By 3:40am my B/P was 120/66 but went back up later with coughing.  I felt fine but tired. A little after 4am,  I carried a bag of apples and a bag of oranges up my stairs and was totally exhausted ? I felt the energy draining out of me, and so was out of breath I dropped the bags on the floor and  sat hyperventilating to get enough air in my lungs until I could breathe normally ? for 40 minutes -  it felt like fluid building in my lungs.  I started massaging my abdomen like crazy and coughing until it subsided ? considering whether I should go to E.R.  My breathing did get some better But I sure did not exert myself.  Just picking up my computer was taking my energy. Still coughing and getting rid of some phlegm.  This was very scary and I was on the verge of going to the E.R.   at 4:45am - I called the E.R. who said I probably could wait for a urgent care to open or talk to Dr.?s office.  My breathing was some better.  By 6:10am I was so tired I fell asleep.   At 10am my B/P was 138/77 p53.  Still very weak, coughing, wheezing, and trying to get rid of phlegm. I had no other symptoms.   I called my Dr. who got me in a urgent care in her building at 3pm.  That evening I started Postural Drainage which helped in getting rid of the phlegm.  I have continued that still. March 16 ? I ?chatted? my doctor to let her know all that was going on.  She scheduled me to see the Respiratory office in her building on the next day.  I was feeling much better ? little nasal dripping, lungs felt better,  March 17 ? Wednesday ? went to Respiratory appt but declined treatment because I felt so much better. More energy, better lungs than Tuesday, wheezing gone, less phlegm, still some coughing ? which is okay with me.  I think this is a severe enough reaction that I should not have the second dose ? which is known to be more severe than the first.

I spoke to some friends and a few of them suprisingly also reported extra heavy menstrual cycles or feeling like they were PMSing around 48 hours after. I couldn't find much online except for a bunch of random people complaining about the same thing, and no study or source of significance to back it. I'm wondering if this something they even looked out for? There seems to be a pretty strong correlation with certain people around my age just from asking around. And I don't think anyone who I spoke to even realized it could be connected until I mentioned it. It was just shocking and significant to me because I'm on set pills that I didn't miss, with no menstrual cycle issues, and I haven't bled more than spotting in years until this. SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Friday, March 12, 2021, at the pharmacy I had an 8:00 am appointment to receive the Johnson & Johnson?s Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine. I received my vaccine in the left arm but the injection seemed to me (and my wife) to be in an odd location, which was very high up on the shoulder near the shoulder joint. Things seemed fine until Saturday evening when I started to feel some tightness in my left trapezius between my scapula and my occipital bone. By Sunday morning that same area was very tight and painful; what we used call a ?crick.? Sunday afternoon I began to feel some sharp pain in my left shoulder joint. I had very little sleep on Sunday night and by Monday morning I had significant pain in what felt like my humerus.  I made an appointment with a chiropractor  for Monday afternoon and he suggested the vaccine shot might have started an inflammation that led to the tight trapezius, which in turn was causing the cervical spinal nerves to react, thus causing the pain in my arm. At this point I was in a lot of pain and the pain was moving further down toward my elbow. The chiropractor did his usual things and told me to put ice on it and take OCT Ibuprofen and or Naproxen. I was a bit better on Tuesday and decided to attend a three-day pastors? retreat. By Tuesday afternoon the pain had expanded to just below my elbow. I consulted with a doctor friend and he thought it was likely that I was having a reaction to the vaccine and that it would pass. He as concerned to hear of the odd location of my injection. I had another sleepless night and on Wednesday I noticed that the ends of my left thumb and index finder were numb and by that night the numbness had expanded to include most of my index finder. The other arm and shoulder pain continued but varied in intensity. On Wednesday morning I called my wife and asked her to come get me at the retreat and that afternoon I called my doctor's office office and made an appointment for Thursday morning (3-18-21). I'm  feeling the cumulative effects of the pain and fatigue. My overall pain level is a little less but still present, as is the numbness in my index finger and thumb. My doctor suggested the nerve inflammation was a reaction tot he vaccine.
OTHER_MEDS: Lantus 100 UNIT/ML Inject 40 units subcutaneous daily   Atorvastatin 40mg Take 1 tablet by mouth daily oral daily   Metoprolol Tartrate 25mg 1 tablet with food orally twice a day   GlyBURIDE 5mg 1 tablet orally two times a day   Ramipril 10

Talked to Dr.  and she said to keep taking Tylenol, a lukewarm bath, lots of fluids and continue to monitor fever. If gets to 102, then would be of concern. Around noon I was feeling a little better, took a nap, and woke up with 101 fever so I took a bath and that helped my temp drop. Between the bath and about 7pm I felt better again. Before bed, my temp jumped up again to 100 but woke up in the morning with no fever. Felt good most of the day Sunday until later afternoon where I had stomach/intestinal pain and just overall fatigue. Rested the rest of the night. Felt normal on Monday. From the date of vaccination- Tuesday my arm was sore and had a little bit of swelling.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Rapid onset significant swelling (lymphedema) in front of left ear and just behind left jawbone.  Began around 10:45am on March 13, by 11am the swelling was at least one inch, enough to distort left side of face and upper neck.  For context, I had been outside planting seedlings that morning and assumed a bug bite, but could not find any puncture wound consistent with a bite.  Alarmed, I immediately took a single benadryl tablet (over the counter) and gently massaged the area (during a zoom conference call!  Turned to my side so as to not alarm my colleagues!!).  I started to feel some drainage about 25 minutes later, and took a second benadryl around 12:15pm.  By late afternoon minimal swelling still present and left point of jawbone sore to touch.  Took one more benadryl  in the evening. Minor swelling but not disforming in the AM, took a final benadryl and by Sunday night March 14 the lyphedema was gone.   As I am a research psychologist, I started looking at the literature and reputable online resources early in the week (March 15/16/17); I found other reports of lymphedema post Moderna vaccine, noted reports that it is on the same side of the face/neck/chest as the vaccine (as it was in my case), and I concluded that THIS is the most likely cause of the swelling I experienced.  I had not ingested ANY food/drink that was new to me during this time, and, as previously stated, there was NO entry wound indicating a bug bite.   Thus, I am making this report to VAERS.  Please note my history of pulmonary sarcoidosis (in remission 20+ years) suggesting I have autoimmune issues, possibly.  I also suffer from Reyes Phenomenon (NOT the disease).  Intriguing, huh?
LAB_DATA: None,  self-treated and resolved.  MD NOT notified.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The first day I got my vaccine, I felt  fine, but my arm with the injection sight was very sore and body slightly achy. The second day I woke up and my arm was sore, but other than that I felt normal. Around 4pm on the second day, my back started to hurt where the break break in my spine is. It was just a normal amount of pain at first, but within an hour there was throbbing pain in my lower back, spreading into my legs. This is where I normally feel my chronic pain, but I had a spinal injection a little over 6 months ago and doesn't usually stop working until about a year. It is the normal pain I experience in the normal places, but the pain is worse and out of no where. That is not usually how the pain comes on when the spinal block wears off. It is much more gradual. It could be a coincidence, but the pain is not the way I have ever experienced the pain.  My back hurts too much to do things I need to do to function, which only happens to me when I have done something with a lot of physical activity that puts tension on my back like jumping, dancing, roller coasters. Before I started experiencing this pain, it was just a normal day for me where I didn't exert my back any more than normal, which is very little.
HISTORY: I have a chronic back problem called spondylosis, where there is a break in-between my 4th and 5th vertebrae.  The break then pushes into my spinal cord, pinching nerves in that area, and causing pain in my lower back and back of my legs. I am treated about every year or two with steroid injections in my spines. I got one less than a year ago, and don't usually start experiencing immense pain until it wears off after about a year.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient had appointment at 9:20 am. She was fine during the check in process, while receiving the imz and the 15 mins post vaccination wait time. Approx 10 am she left the IMZ room and about halfway through the store, she fainted. CSM said the fell outside of patient's room and did not seem to hit her head or neck. 911 wasn't called because she came to right away. They got her water and a chair. I was brought over approx 10:10 am. I talked with her and she seemed cognitive, lucid and understands who she is, where she is and what happened. She said she waited the 15 min and felt totally fine but then she got up and fell about halfway through store. Approx 10:20 am we brought her over to pharmacy area for more privacy and RPH checked her BP. reported 130/90. I asked patient if she wanted the paramedics called just in case of a head injury. I asked her before palpating her head and neck. She said she felt no pain, no visible bleeding or lacerations, no inflammation or redness and she has full mobility in her neck with no pain. Patient said she did not want paramedics called and instead called her mother in law who lives nearby to see if they can come get her. She is worried about  40 min drive home. Pt overall physically seemed fine. She was just shaken, nervous and embarrassed as she's never had something like this happen before. She waited for about 20 mins until her father in law came and picked her up. I updated him of the situation and they left together.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a 78-year-old male with history of COPD, paroxysmal atrial fibrillation, ischemic cardiomyopathy, type 2 diabetes mellitus, status post mitral valve replacement with metallic valve on Coumadin, stage II: CAD status post LAR.  Presented to Hospital campus on account of severe shortness of breath in a patient with significant weakness.  Patient has had significant shortness of breath progressively worsening.  Patient was just discharged from this facility on 03/17/2021.  The patient was admitted on 03/05/201 on account of shortness of breath.  During the admission, patient had a multiloculated right-sided pleural effusion requiring video-assisted thoracoscopy and evacuation of hemothorax.  Associated with chest wall mass.  Subsequent biopsy revealed evidence of small cell carcinoma.  The patient was seen by oncology during that admission with a Mediport put in place.  With plans to follow-up with oncology outpatient for continued management and to hopefully initiate chemotherapy.  There was also concern for acute congestive heart failure and required diuresis.  Echocardiogram was showing EF of 40% at the time.  Now, patient is presented to the emergency room on account of significant weakness in the patient well developed worsening shortness of breath over the last couple of days.  Patient was still short of breath and weak he could not even get up the toilet seat.  When EMS saw the patient he was satting 80% on room air and required  6 L via nasal cannula.  Did not complain of any chest pain or cough with this finding.  Neither did he complain of any fever.  In the emergency room, patient was tachypneic and slightly tachycardic.  Lab work shows lactic acid of 2.3 glucose of 302 and creatinine of 1.90.  The patient's BNP was 1170 with GFR of 34.  Patient INR was 4.5.  Chest x-ray shows  Trace right pleural effusion. No pneumothorax.  With concern for pneumonia patient was given azithromycin and Unasyn.  Also with concern for possible CHF patient was given Bumex.

Patient presents to the ED on 03/20/21 at ~19:45 for palpitations and shortness of breath. Patient symptoms started 1 hour prior. He woke from sleep sweating, feeling short of breath and having heart pounding sensation. No chest pain. He was seen at Army clinic on base where they were concerned he was in A. fib and brought him to the ED. His VS where slightly hypertensive, tachypnic but not tachycardic with normal temperature and pulse ox. He was given 1L bolus of LR, had EKG, CXR, echo and cardiac stress test done while here. He was discharged in good condition with follow up with cardiology in 4 days for Holter monitor.
LAB_DATA: EKG - showed LVH with strain pattern and inverted T waves in lateral leads. Repeat EKG 15 minutes later was similar. Bedside echo by myself and cardiology showed thickened hypertrophied left ventricle and septum and small pericardial effusion. There is concern for undiagnosed hypertrophic cardiomyopathy given that the patient has had an enlarged heart since the 4th grade. Cardiology did an exercise stress test that showed no abnormality in VS and echo as well showing similar results. He is labs including cardiac enzymes, CBC, CMP, BNP, coags and UA were all within normal limits. He is discharged to return in 4 days for Holter monitor for possible underlying arrhythmia. Likely this is all chronic secondary to long standing hypertension vs. undiagnosed hypertrophic cardiomyopathy

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my shot at 11:47 and started to lose sensation in my hands in the waiting area. After about 25 minutes I felt dizzy and was about to stand up but my muscles started shaking. My heart rate was checked and found to be 140. This lasted for about another 30 minutes. My heart rate went down and I was taken to a private area and checked out by EMS they gave me water and concluded it was some sort of panic attack. However, these are the same symptoms I have whenever I am allergic to a medication, NSAIDS, dicyclomine, etc. It always starts with ascending numbness from my fingers to the rest of my body. Then I start to shake and my heart rate goes way up. Usually I start to cough then vomit and my airway closes. Thankfully this time we were able to slow the process and I never experienced some of the last symptoms.

On Thursday, March 18, I had some slight dizziness during the day. After going to bed that night I woke up and the night light in the smoke alarm on the ceiling appeared to be spinning. I sat, then stood, grabbling walls for support and attempted to reach my recliner. At that point I was severely dizzy, completely lost any sense of balance and collapsed into the chair. I could not stand or walk. After 20 minutes, I asked my wife to call an ambulance. I did not think she would be able to get me into our car. The paramedics ran an EKG and tested me for a stroke. Both were normal. I was transported to the ER. The doctor gave me Meclizine. Had a CT scan of my brain, and blood work. All results normal. Dizziness resolved. They tested my balance and then released me at 3:30 a.m. on March 19. I was tired that day, but did not need further medication. During that night, as I turned over in bed, the vertigo returned. I took a Meclizine and went to the recliner for the remainder of the night. I am feeling somewhat fuzzy today, March 20. Not sure how long this will continue, or if it is related to my Covid vaccination. However, I am reporting it in the event that others may be experiencing this problem as well.
OTHER_MEDS: Tamsulosin, Oxybutynin, Omeprazole, Escitalopram, Atorvastatin, Telmisartan, Hydrochlorothiazide

On February 14, I checked my Nexplanon birth control and could feel it in my left arm. Around February 15, I started getting some soreness around my nexplanon birth control in my left arm. I was able to get seen Student Health & Counseling on February 17. We noticed there was some swelling and bruising around my birth control and we could not find the nexplanon itself. We also noticed a little knot right next to my birth control as well. I was sent to the emergency room where they found the birth control and sent me home. I went back to the Student Health & Counseling to talk about my next options on getting it out on February 19th. We took some blood work to make sure everything was alright. My doctor was worried that the knot in my arm might have been a blood clot. She sent me to get an ultrasound where the Doppler said the knot looked like it was swelling. A few hours later, my doctor called me back and told me to go to the emergency room because my d-dimer levels were high. I went to the hospital, they took blood work again and everything came back fine. After a couple of days, the pain and swelling went down but it did cause my nexplanon birth control to migrate in my arm. I got the second vaccine on March 4. On March 5, I noticed soreness in my arm with a little swelling where my birth control was. While it wasn't as severe as the first time, I could definitely tell there was swelling and soreness. This lasted about 2 days.
OTHER_MEDS: Nexplanon birth control in left arm.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Thursday March 11, 2021 I received my first dose of Pfizer COVID vaccine. Within about 5 second after administration I began to feel severe arm pain spreading from the injection site down to my fingers that were tingling and numb. Then within about 20 seconds of the vaccine I  fainted.   The fainting spell was brief, a few seconds, but the symptoms that continued after were long lasting.  My blood pressure after was about 80/50, I was diaphoretic, pale, had moderate arm pain (tingling, numb, painful to move) and severe nausea. I was also light headed. These symptoms lasted through the night but I felt overall improved the next day other than fatigue and lingering arm pain. Then on March 16, 2021, 5 days later, I woke up with extreme fatigue. Over the course of the day I then began to get a headache. I got back in bed and then in the afternoon started to feel moderate arm pain again at the injection site and down the entire arm. Then severe nausea set in again along with more diaphoresis, chills and light headedness. The symptoms this time again lasted through the night and I felt better again the next morning.
PRIOR_VAX: I have vasovagaled twice before this time. Once with HPV when I was around 18 years old and another time when I was around grade

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Upper middle and lower right abdominal pains that were consistent and nothing helped - random spurts of increased pain. 6 days after no relief, I made an appointment with a gastrointestinal doctor. On day 8, I had vomiting and multiple episodes of diarrhea. I saw the doctor on day 9 but there was so much all-over abdominal pain, it was difficult to decipher the cause. A ct scan was ordered but needed authed by the insurance. On day 10 of symptoms with no reflief, I went to the ER. After a ct scan, it was determined that appendicitis was present for probably 10 days which lead to a perforated appendix with abscess and inflammation around the appendix. While admitted to the hospital for 3 days, I was treated with IV antibiotics but the appendix could not be removed due to so much inflammation and abscess. I have a follow up in a few weeks to remove the appendix once another ct scan determines the area is cleared up.

PI:  The pt is a 40 year old female who presents with syncope 20 minutes post Moderna dose #1 vaccination to the left deltoid. Pt syncopized from a seated position, falling forward and catching herself with her arms outstretched. +LOC before immediately regaining consciousness. No head or neck injury, +abrasion to the left elbow. Pt notes similar episode following an influenza vaccine 15 years ago. Pt denies any medical Hx, daily medications, or Hx of anaphylaxis. Pt denies swelling or itching of the lips, eyes, or face. She also denies any swelling of throat, difficulty breathing, or SOB.  Exam (update as needed): GEN: Alert and oriented x 3 upon immediate evaluation,  HEAD: NCAT EYES: PERRL, EOMI ENT: Ears normal, Nose normal, OP normal, no evidence of angioedema NECK: Supple, without LAD.  CV: RRR,+Bradycardic, +hypotensive, no m/r/g PULM:  Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no accessory muscle use ABD: Soft, no tenderness. SKIN: +pale, +diaphoretic, +1cm circular abrasion to left elbow, No rashea MSK: FROM, MS 5/5 NEURO: Alert and oriented x 4, CN 2-12 grossly intact, no ataxia   Clinical Impression/Field Tx: Syncope post moderna does #1 vaccination. Impression supported by clinical scenario, vital signs, and Pt?s endorsement of similar incident in the past, Suspicion for anaphylaxis low due to no signs of angioedema, no SOB, and no complaints of itching. Pt also denied any Hx of anaphylaxis or allergic reaction. Vital signs stabilized in the field and pt reported improvement following 30 minutes of repositioning and observation. Because of limited resources on site, the Pt was evaluated by EMS where repeat vital signs, blood glucose, and EKG were obtained.    Medications administered: None     Disposition:  Pt was evaluated by EMS and transported to the  Hospital.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I tested positive for COVID on January 24th.  I never had a fever throuhgout my illness; however I did have mild cold symptoms, and lost all sense of taste and smell.  My taste and smell just started to return a few weeks ago.   I received the Pfizer vaccine on Friday, March 12th.  On Monday, March 15th, I lost all smell and taste.  When I completed a virtual care visit, I was advised that since I had COVID within the past 12 weeks, I was not eligible to be retested for COVID.  However, I was informed that loss of taste and smell were not side effects of the vaccine and that I needed to go home and quarantine for 2 weeks.    I requested a second opinion, and was instructed from my second opinion to get retested (although this was against routine CDC guidelines).  My retest was negative for COVID.  I have been advised that my loss of taste and smell should be reported to the CDC as a side effect of the vaccine.  I still do not have taste or smell as of March 20.
LAB_DATA: I was retested (PCR) for COVID on March 17th ---- results for COVID were negative.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About a minute after I had the injection, my arm started hurting and it felt like hot water was coursing through my veins. The nurses said I went pale and they called it a panic attack, but it was unlike any panic attack I have ever had in my life. I?ve had my TDAP updated a few years ago and got a flu shot and did not feel anything like this. I was rolled out of the room on a wheel chair because I was too dizzy to walk and then threw up several times into a bag and peed myself. It took about 20 minutes before I felt normal again.   The following day my arm felt numb and incredibly sore, I couldn?t raise it that far up without excruciating pain. I felt weak, fatigued and dizzy and was unable to use the bathroom. I had fever sweats and chills on and off. I was not able to sleep well, but I think that?s because of the pain in my arm.
HISTORY: Back pain, anxiety, depression, knee pain

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Back started itching then front stomach area and spreed to both side and neck. then hives started appearing. followed by Jagged spots with white ares and jagged round ring. Welt on rump x. chills, on and off. followed buy hot spot ankle side of shins and side of thighs. Went to ER  IV Benadryl Took blood sample. Did CBC & Differential. Comprehensive Metabolic Panel. After a few hours the Red color in my forearm started to disappearing. Gave me a prescription for Benadryl and Famotidine 20mg ,Prednisone 50mg. Returned to ER next day as swelling started back up. IV Benadryl sent me home. No improvement. Dr  changed to Hydroxyzine 25mg. home no improvement and Most of my body was covered. I had hot spot   Hot spots feet, shins, thigh, fore arms. Put wet towels on hot spots to stop pain and itching. change ever 30 minutes no sleep for days Finally got in to DR  he increased the famotidine to 40mg. Around 3am I finally slept, When I woke My lip was swollen and my throat was tight had a lump in it. drank water and ate a cookie. would not clear gaged down the Medication some dissolved before I could get them down. Drove to the hospital. They gave me injection in my thigh and IV Benadryl. Added Loratadine and had me get a Epinephrine Pen. Dr  increased the medication. Very slowly the welt, and hives started changing to red rash, hot spots and itching continued. only got short sleep during the day and night at times exhausted. coughed several times for minute non stop. Slight fever followed by chills and some shaking. Very nervous at times. As thing started getting better I took some pictures. Could not believe what my body was going threw. March 18 finaly starting to go away getting better skin wise but still cold and hot. Mouth all this time would go from no taste to bad taste. Throw up feeling at times had to fight it off. March 16,17, after I would fall asleep I had very bad pounding headache took Aspirin and Tylenol. after three hours put a wet towel on my forehead. finally let up and was able to sleep a little. the second night same thing except after I went to sleep the towel dropped my core temperature could not get warm took temp 94.4. Turned heat back up to 78 degrees Wrapped upper body as had to keep lower legs in open air with wet towels on hot spots. Stopped taking my Blood Pressure and switch to from Hydroxyzine to (Banophen Diphenhydramin ) The spots are finally getting smaller. Feet are still swollen and are hard to walk on, still have to go everywhere in open slippers and pant legs rolled up. blisters broke on ankle finally getting better. March 20 left foot still swollen and stiff, right foot swelling going down a little. I could not handle filling this out until now. My memory and even my eye site was affected. I had to write it down in case some one asked me. When they asked me I couldnt remember everything. has to look and my notes to remember. Finally got a referral to infectious disease and a allergist.
LAB_DATA: CBC and differential 03/04/21 Comprehensiv metabolic panel 03/04/21

As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of the product, the pt suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the pt had suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. All damage proximately caused by the aforementioned characteristics of the zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) product that rendered the product unreasonably dangerous, arose from the reasonably anticipated use of the product by the the pt. The outcome of the event was not recovered. The causality assessment was considered as related by the lawyer.  The lawyer considered the event painful outbreak of shingles to be disability.

immobilizing pain in my left hip; full body muscle spasms; hip pain was almost unbearable; 101.5 temp; blood preassure was 155/110 / my blood pressure was 168/130, 165/128, and 171/130; swelling at injection site; soreness at injection site; pain muscle of my right hip; major night sweating; a bit of fatigue late in the afternoon; This case was reported by a consumer and described the occurrence of fever in a 60-year-old male patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   On 9th February 2021 14:00, the patient received the 1st dose of Shingrix. In February 2020, less than 2 weeks after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced fatigue. On 9th February 2021, the patient experienced mobility decreased and muscle spasm. In February 2021, the patient experienced fever, increased blood pressure, injection site swelling, injection site pain, muscle pain, sweating and pain in hip. The patient was treated with tramadol and ibuprofen (Advil). On an unknown date, the outcome of the fever, increased blood pressure, injection site swelling, injection site pain, muscle pain, sweating, mobility decreased, muscle spasm, pain in hip and fatigue were recovered/resolved.   The reporter considered the fever, increased blood pressure, injection site swelling, injection site pain, muscle pain, sweating, mobility decreased, muscle spasm, pain in hip and fatigue to be related to Shingrix.  Additional details were provided as follows: The patient received Shingrix in left arm at around 2:00 pm and five hours later had a 101.5 temperature, blood pressure was 155/110, swelling and soreness at injection site. The patient had a 10 level pain in the muscle of right hip.  These symptoms persisted for four days and included major night sweating, continued immobilizing pain in left hip and full body muscle spasms. The patient reported after each of these spasms blood pressure was 168/130, 165/128 and 171/130 and the hip pain was almost unbearable.  The patient took two 50mg Tramadol and Advil and went to sleep.  The patient when woke up on Saturday and it was like nothing ever happened.  The hip pain was completely gone, blood pressure was normal (128/90), the swelling at the injection site was gone and the fever was down to 99. The patient had X-rays of hip that showed no ortho problems and did not had any lingering effects except a bit of fatigue. The doctor was not convinced that the issues are related to Shingrix, but there were no underlying issues and the symptoms all showed up on the day of the vaccination and all pretty much went away on the same day. The patient experience was less than perfect and wanted to share it in hopes that the patient at least confirm that my health issues side effects are related to vaccination.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: chest pain; signs of super ventricular tachycardia; swelling on the right side of my face; Frequent palpitations; From the knees down, both legs felt numb into her feet; Could not stand; shortness of breath; Premature ventricular contractions; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 55-years-old female patient , who received  Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine(mRNA-1273)  and experienced the following: chest pain, could not stand (dysstasia), shortness of breath (dyspnea), signs of supraventricular tachycardia (supraventricular tachycardia), swelling on the right side of face (swelling face), from the knees down, both legs felt numb into the feet (hypoaesthesia) , frequent palpitations (palpitations), premature ventricular contractions, a lot of them (ventricular extrasystole).  The patient's medical history was not provided. Relevant concomitant medications as reported included metoprolol .  On 29 Jan 2021, prior to the onset of events, the patient received their second of two planned doses  of  mRNA-1273(Lot/batch:013L20A) intramuscularly in the left deltoid for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On an unspecified date the patient experienced events swelling on the right side of face , signs of supraventricular tachycardia , frequent palpitations . On 01 Feb 2021, the patient experienced shortness of breath and a lot of premature ventricular contractions (this was confirmed by patient's doctor on an EKG).  On 05 Feb 2021, the patient reported they were starting to get in trouble. They woke up on 06 Feb 2021 with chest pain and very short of breath. From the knees down, both legs felt numb into the feet. By the end of the day, the patient could not stand. The patient's cardiologist prescribed metoprolol which was helping some. On an unknown date, the patient ended up in the emergency room (ER) with chest pain.  An echocardiogram didn't show much. The last week of February 2021 (dates unspecified) the patient reported they went to the ER again for chest pain. At that time, the numbness and tingling had gone away. The patient was admitted for two nights to the local hospital and while there had a poor exercise test and signs of superventricular tachycardia. Treatment included an increase in metoprolol, but the patient still had frequent palpitations. Metoprolol was again increased to control and monitor the heart. The patient is wearing a heart monitor.    The patient received both scheduled doses of mRNA-1273 prior to the event(s); therefore, action taken with the drug in response to the event(s) is not applicable.  At the time of the report, the outcome of the events ,swelling on the right side of face,signs of supraventricular tachycardia , frequent palpitations, shortness of breath, premature ventricular contractions, chest pain, and could not stand, was unknown .  At the time of the report, the outcome of the event from the knees down both legs felt numb into the feet, was considered resolved .; Reporter's Comments: The events were consistent with increased risk of cardiovascular complications associated with age of patient. Company assessed the events to be unlikely related to company product.
HISTORY: Medical History/Concurrent Conditions: No adverse event (No medical history provided)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: tightening in his throat muscle; unable to move much; unstable blood pressure; unstable oxygen; bled due to blood thinner; weak in terms of walking; coughing; every joint and muscle from neck to toe in pain; every joint and muscle from neck to toe in pain; cold; entire body in excruciating pain; A bit off; Bruising in arm; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 83-year-old male patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced the following events: bruising in arm (contusion), a bit off (feeling abnormal), entire body in excruciating pain (pain), every joint and muscle from neck to toe in pain (arthralgia/myalgia), tightening in his throat muscle (throat tightness), unable to move much (hypokinesia), unstable blood pressure (blood pressure abnormal), unstable oxygen (oxygen saturation abnormal), bled due to blood thinner (haemorrhage), cold (feeling cold), weak in terms of walking (muscular weakness), and coughing (cough),   The patient's medical history included small cancer treated last year with 38 radiation treatments. No concomitant medications were reported.  On 11 Feb 2021, prior to the onset of the events the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch: 031620A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection.  On 11 Feb 2021, the patient experienced little bruising in the arm. On 12 Feb 2021, the patient was a bit off. On Sunday, 28 Feb 2021, in the evening, the patient got cold, and within minutes his entire whole body was in excruciating pain, every joint and muscle from neck to toe were in pain. It felt like it was invaded with COVID. He went to hospital and got tested for COVID, Strep throat and Flu, and all three test results were negative. On an unknown date, the patient experienced tightening in his throat muscle and he went to the hospital where he was admitted.  While there, they did every possible test, chest MRI, Neck MRI, all possible viral tests, and rapid and full COVID test.  The rapid and full COVID tests came back negative.  Results for chest MRI, neck MRI and viral tests were not provided.  The hospital also performed a blood culture for bacteria. Results were not provided.  The patient was unable to move much, his blood pressure and oxygen were a little unstable. On 06 Mar 2021, the hospital did a major blood test which came back negative and the patient was released from a hospital. He stated that he was still weak in terms of walking and coughing. He stated that he recently bled due to taking blood thinner.  Treatment included major antibiotic treatments and steroids for pain during the hospital stay. The patient was still taking prednisone at a tapering dose.  Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown.   The events of weak in terms of walking, coughing were unresolved, while the outcome of the events of tightening in his throat muscle, unable to move much, unstable blood pressure, unstable oxygen, bled due to blood thinner, Bruising in arm, cold, entire body in excruciating pain, every joint and muscle from neck to toe in pain, every joint and muscle from neck to toe in pain was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on a strong temporal association between the reported events and administration of mRNA-1273 vaccine, a causal association cannot be excluded.  Myalgia and arthralgia are consistent with the known safety profile of the vaccine

SYMPTOM_TEXT: SIRVA; A PHASE 1/2/3, PLACEBO-CONTROLLED, RANDOMIZED, OBSERVER-BLIND, DOSE-FINDING STUDY TO EVALUATE THE SAFETY, TOLERABILITY, IMMUNOGENICITY, AND EFFICACY OF SARS-COV-2 RNA VACCINE CANDIDATES AGAINST COVID-19 IN HEALTHY INDIVIDUALS  This is a report from an interventional study source sponsored by BioNTech, managed and reported by Pfizer on the sponsors behalf. A 30-year-old female subject received the first dose of blinded vaccine (BNT162; PLACEBO) on 17Aug2020 at 17:01 and second dose on 09Sep2020 at 15:20, both intramuscularly on the left deltoid as single doses for COVID-19 immunization. Medical history included ongoing allergies. Ongoing concomitant medication included cetirizine hydrochloride (ZYRTEC) for allergies. The subject had no other vaccine administered neither on the same day nor within four weeks prior to the administration of the investigational vaccine and no relevant family medical history. The subject had no history of trauma, heavy lifting or vigorous exercise, and the subject was believed to be right-handed. On 09Sep2020 at 18:00, the subject experienced shoulder injury related to vaccine administration (SIRVA) after the second vaccine dose, which was considered as a medically significant event and required physician office visit. The clinical course was as follows: on 09Sep2020 at evening, the subject had pain in the whole left arm. She noted that the band-aid was very high on her arm. She had some soreness of her upper arm and very limited range of motion for the first few days, with burning pain down her arm. Initially she had some tingling down her arm, but this had resolved. On 15Sep2020, the subject had a sensation of numbness which affected her arm and hand, with a sensation of loss of dexterity which was notable when typing. The subject informed that she was improving gradually, especially in terms of pain, but still had a significant limitation in range of motion and daily activities. On exam she did not have any obvious swelling, color change, bruising, or tenderness over the left deltoid. She could raise her left arm slightly higher than 90 degrees and with assistance could lift higher, but this caused significant discomfort. She could not extent her left arm behind her back well. Strength was 5/5. When moving her arm against resistance, she experienced pain down her arm and increased sensation of numbness. The investigator discussed a possible diagnosis of SIRVA. The subject was aware that it could be self-limiting and might last for some time. The subject was seen by a neurologist who noted the following findings: motor function: normal muscle bulk and tone. No apparent fasciculations. No scapular winging. Shoulder abduction limited to 70 degrees; shoulder internal rotation limited as well but able to put her left hand behind her back. An electromyography (EMG) was recommended to determine if nerve involvement and if so, to what degree. Physical therapy was also recommended which the neurologist noted that the subject had already started. There was no neurophysiologic evidence of a cervical radiculopathy on the left. Clinical correlation was recommended". On 07Oct2020, the neurologist considered that SIRVA was the most likely diagnosis based on the clinical improvement and that the EMG result did not reveal nerve involvement in the neurons tested. The subject reported continued improvement especially of the upper arm with increased range of motion but continued decreased dexterity of the left hand. The subject was attending physical therapy twice weekly and reported satisfaction with the gradual and continued improvement the subject was experiencing. On 03Nov2020, the subject informed that she had completed 5 weeks of physical therapy, that her improvement was significant but that she was not back to her usual state of health. The action taken with the blinded vaccine (BNT162; PLACEBO) in response to the event was not applicable.  Subject was felt much better and had returned to baseline after completing physical therapy. The outcome of the event was completely recovered on 08Feb2021.  The investigator considered there was a reasonable possibility that the event SIRVA was related to the second dose blinded vaccine (BNT162; PLACEBO) and to a clinical trial procedure (vaccine administration) but considered it unrelated to concomitant medications.  On 21Sep2020, the blinded code was broken due to serious, related, unexpected event. No further information provided.  Follow-up (09Mar2021): New information reported includes: adverse reaction (event onset date specified, outcome of event updated to recovered) and clinical course. ; Sender's Comments: The event SIRVA is unlisted in the Single Reference Safety Document (SRSD) of the Investigational Product blinded therapy vaccine (BNT162; PLACEBO) based on the information currently available.  There is a reasonable possibility for the event SIRVA to be related with the blinded therapy vaccine (BNT162; PLACEBO). Based on the reported location of the band-aid, i.e., high up on the subject's arm, and the occurrence of the SIRVA, it appears that the vaccine was erroneously administered into or near the shoulder joint capsule. Postulated in the medical literature, unintentional injection of vaccines into the shoulder joint synovial tissues may result in an immune-mediated inflammatory reaction causing SIRVA. Reports of SIRVA has been associated with poor techniques in administering vaccines in general. The event is not considered a unique response to this specific vaccine (BNT162; PLACEBO).  The impacts of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product and on the conduct of the study is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to Regulatory Authorities, Ethics Committee and Investigators, as appropriate.

It was reported that investigation was required. The sample of the product was not available to be returned. It was reported (RESPONSE FROM employee: Per attached CONS) the covid-19 vaccine will not make you test positive for the infection, the COVID-19 vaccine might not protect everyone, the efficacy information sated that the vaccine has a 95% efficacy 7 days after the second dose. Referred to her physician for treatment recommendations. No reasonably suggest device malfunction. Severity of Harm and Failure Mode: N/A. FPRS Evaluation Comment: Pfizer reviewed this complaint and agrees with the site assignment, investigation decision, classification, sub-classification, and priority. The reported lot number is valid and an investigation will be performed. No repeat investigation, no CAPA previously identified, and full investigation Required. QA Review & Rationale: The complaint and its classification have been reviewed. No immediate containment action is required. The complaint, its priority, and its classification have been reviewed and determined to be appropriate. A full investigation will be performed. This is a complaint for lack of effect of lot EM9809 of the PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE. The initial scope of this investigation is limited to the reported finished goods lot EM9809 pending review of lot genealogy. The investigation will include a review of the returned complaint sample (if received) and reserve samples, if necessary. Investigation Findings (Summary of Investigation): The initial scope of the investigation was limited to the reported finished goods lot. The final scope was expanded to include the reported finished goods lot EM9809, fill lot EM9807, and the formulated drug product lot EM9805. Manufacturing and packaging batch records were reviewed for the reported complaint lot. Pfizer (Site name) QO did not receive photographs or a complaint sample for examination. The complaint was not confirmed. There were no planned or unplanned deviations recorded during the manufacture of the complaint lot and associated manufacturing lots that may have caused a complaint of this nature. A review of the manufacturing records confirmed processing steps were performed within pre-established parameters. All raw materials and amounts used in the manufacture of the batch were of the correct weight and identity. The drug product is stored at controlled refrigeration throughout the manufacturing process and a log is maintained documenting the elapsed time out of refrigeration. A review of the logs confirmed that all times were within allowable limits. The product also requires storage in ultra-low temperature freezers following the packaging of the product. A review of the freezer temperature log for the reported batch confirmed that all freezer temperatures were within allowable limits. The results of all analytical tests performed at the time of lot release confirmed that the batch continues to meet potency specifications. Root Cause/CAPA: not process/ vendor related and Final Confirmation Status: Not Confirmed. Root Cause Analysis/Identif: Operations could not indicate a probable root cause for the complaint to be related to the production process of the involved batch. Review of the manufacturing and packaging batch records and release test results confirmed that the batch continues to meet potency specifications. It is unknown how the product was handled, stored, or administered after it left the Pfizer site. Impact Analysis: Based on the results of this investigation, the manufacturing and packaging batches remain acceptable and the reported complaint is not representative of the lot. No regulatory notification is needed. Improve/Control: Corrective / Preventive Action: There were no corrective actions as a result of this complaint investigation. The results of all tests, inspections, and in-process controls have been reviewed and all results met the established requirements prior to the release of the reported batch for distribution. It was concluded that: The complaint for lack of effect of the PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE lot EM9809 was investigated. The investigation included a review of manufacturing and packaging batch records, deviation investigations, and an analysis of complaint history for the reported lot. The final scope included the reported finished goods lot EM9809, fill lot EM9807, and the formulated drug product lot EM9805. A complaint sample was not returned, and photographs were not received. No related quality issues were identified during the investigation. There is no impact to product quality. No root cause or corrective/preventative actions were identified as the complaint was not confirmed. All release testing performed prior to the release of the reported batch was within specifications. Batch/ Process record review (Scope of Compl. Investigation): The scope of this investigation included the reported finished goods lot EM9809, fill lot EM9807, and the bulk formulated drug product EM9805. Acceptable review of related documentation, including manufacturing batch records and review of release test results at the time of lot release confirmed that there were no issues which may have resulted in a complaint of this nature. Document Review Summary: DEVIATIONS, MANUFACTURING BATCH RECORDS, PACKAGING BATCH RECORDS, and LOT HISTORY were complete (Acceptable).  Reserve Sample Testing Result: A reserve sample was not sent to the QC-lab to determine the amount of active ingredient since the complaint was received within six months of the release date of the involved batch. The results of all analytical tests performed at the time of lot release were confirmed to be within registered specifications. All available stability results for this product were within registered specification and stability studies (including accelerated studies) are ongoing for this product. No confirmed Reserve Defect. Lot Trend Actions Taken: There were no lot trend actions taken as a result of this investigation. Sample site status was not received.

Pre-term delivery at 36.6 weeks of gestational age; Vaccine exposure during pregnancy; Low potassium; This observational study case was received from other health professional  on 30-Nov-2020 and concerned a 35-year-old pregnant, female subject of body weight 108 lbs, height 62 inches and body mass index (BMI) 19.8, enrolled in a prospective observational safety study on pregnancy outcomes in women immunized with Afluria QIV during pregnancy.   The subject's medical history included advanced maternal age. The subject's concomitant medications included Prenatal vitamins (unspecified vitamins and mineral) for healthy pregnancy.  The subject's obstetrical history included three previous pregnancies with one full term live birth and two elective abortions. The subject had no history of offspring with major congenital malformation (MCM). The subject had no maternal or paternal medical history with MCMs. The subject did not use tobacco, alcohol or illicit drugs during pregnancy.  The subject's last menstrual period (LMP) date was 23-Jun-2020. The subject's estimated delivery date (EDD) was reported as 30-Mar-2021 and corrected estimated date of delivery (CEDD) was not reported. The type of pregnancy was singleton.  On 02-Sep-2020, at approximately ten weeks of gestation (calculated per LMP), the subject was vaccinated with Afluria QIV (Flu Vaccine Egg Split QIV CSL) (influenza vaccine; dose, route of administration and  anatomical location: not reported) (explicitly coded as 'Vaccine exposure during pregnancy') for influenza immunisation. The batch number reported was P100239705.  On an unknown date in Sep-2020, an unknown amount of time after receiving Afluria Quadrivalent, the subject had low potassium.   On 18-Sep-2020, panorama test revealed no MCMs.    On 19-Sep-2020, first trimester screen revealed no MCMs.   On 21-Sep-2020, the subject started treatment for low potassium with potassium chlorate, at a dose of 20 mcg, three times a day, administered orally.   On 03-Nov-2020, amniocentesis revealed no MCMs.  On 06-Nov-2020, the subject finished the treatment with potassium chloride.  On 07-Mar-2021, at gestational age of 36.6 weeks (as reported), the subject delivered premature live male neonate via vaginal method of delivery. The birth weight of the neonate was 2781 g, head circumference 32 cm and length 49.5 cm. Appearance, pulse, grimace, activity and respiration (APGAR) score at one minute was 9, at five minutes was 9 and at ten minutes was not reported. No pregnancy complications were noted. No MCM was identified at birth.  The outcome of the event 'premature delivery' was not reported.  At the time of follow up reporting on 10-Dec-2020, the subject had not recovered from the event of 'potassium low'.   The reporter did not provide a causality assessment.  The event of 'premature delivery' was considered to be medically significant by a Physician within Seqirus's Pharmacovigilance and Risk Management Department.  The case is linked to the case 202101842 (corresponding baby case).  Additional information received from other health professional on 10-Dec-2020: The subject was enrolled in pregnancy registry and report type was changed from spontaneous to report from study. The subject's ID amended. LMP date and EDD were provided. The narrative was amended accordingly.  Additional information received from other health professional on 25-Feb-2021 with an additional document received on the same day (being processed together): Type of pregnancy provided and number of fetus populated in pregnancy information. Stop date for treatment medication potassium chloride provided. Narrative was amended accordingly.  Additional information received on 09-Mar-2021 from other health professional: Pregnancy outcome received. New event added, premature delivery. Stop date was added for the event of 'vaccine exposure during pregnancy' and outcome was changed from 'Not reported' to 'Resolved'. Pregnancy with advanced maternal age added in medical history. The narrative was amended accordingly.   Company comment: A 35-year-old pregnant, female subject experienced blood potassium decreased 18 days after administration of Afluria QIV and premature delivery six months after vaccination. The subject's medical history included advanced maternal age. The subject's obstetrical history included three previous pregnancies with one full term live birth and two elective abortions. Causality is assessed as unrelated due to biological implausibility and confounding factors (advanced maternal age and obstetrical history). Vaccine exposure during pregnancy is assessed as unrelated per company conventions.; Sender's Comments: A 35-year-old pregnant, female subject experienced blood potassium decreased 18 days after administration of Afluria QIV and premature delivery six months after vaccination. I also had a couple hot flashes to where I woke up sweating. Then I would feel frozen again. The nausea started during the night too. I thought I would throw up but didn't. At one point my heart was racing so fast I was a little concerned something bad would happen to me and contemplated going to the hospital. By morning I felt a little better, still nauseous and with a bad headache. My body was a little weak. These symptoms lasted all day Thursday. By that Friday morning I only had a little weakness and slight headache. By mid day Friday I was pretty much back to normal.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: This was the first shot of the Covid vaccination, brand Pfizer.   The nurse administered the shot in the wrong place entering my rotor cuff tendon of my left arm.   The evening of February 19th, the same day as the shot, I could not lift my arm.   The pain continued throughout the weekend.   My doctor was called on 2/22/21 and the nurse stated that it was SIRVA (shoulder injury related to vaccination).  She said to apply ice to the area and call in two weeks if it didn't feel better.  Went to a chiropractor on 3-5-21 and he did range of motion and said it looks liked an injury however he would recommend a Physical Therapist to examine it further.   He did light shoulder manipulation.   3-8-21, went to Physical Therapist and he confirmed through range of motion that the injury occurred to a tendon located in the rotor cuff area.   He diagnosed it as tendonitis (possible tear) with possible bursitis.    3-10 and 3-11 PT appointments.    3-12-21 second COVID shot in the correct deltoid muscle.  No issues.   3-16 PT appointment.    3-19 -21.   From  favoring my right arm, my lower back went into spasms.   Dr. appt with Doctor over the phone consolation.   Prescription administered.    At this time, therapy will continue.   Previous to the first 2-19-21 shot, I was in perfect health with an A+ doctor physical, worked out weekly, and took no medication.   Since this time, I have been unable to continue to work out, it has effected my lifestyle, and caused continued financial expenses to manage.   This is the 3rd event I have heard of throughout State of the same sort.   The local PT doctor is treating someone for the same thing and a local teacher experienced the same thing at another site.   The training is obviously not in place.
LAB_DATA: Physical Therapist and doctor confirmed through diagnoses.

Reaction started out with a localized 3-4 inch inflamed reaction. It looked very similar to hives. This was on Friday, March 19th, 2021 around 9 PM. I went to sleep and woke up the next morning and it was still there. I took benadryl and one ibuprofen to help the inflammation and the reaction, but it only got worse following this. I then had intense tactile and mechanical allodynia, which is often associated with my diagnosis of fibromyalgia, but this has been very intense. The allodynia had been occurring across my left hand up to my elbow, but has now moved to both of my arms, my neck, my entire back (more severely around the ribs), my chest, and my feet. I am very fatigued and feel feverish. My current temperature is only 99.2, but the pain is still active. Today is Sunday, March 21st, 2021. I got the vaccine on Saturday, March 13th, 2021 and this reaction is following the vaccine about a week after.
HISTORY: Fibromyalgia, Ehlers Danlos Syndrome, Non-Celiac gluten sensitivity, Irritable bowel syndrome

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On the second day after vaccine, about 25 hours later, I threw up, became disoriented, sleepy, and was slurring my words. I continued with my day, not knowing that I was not making sense, and had professional interactions with coworkers and clients, who later reported that I sounded confused, sleepy, and disoriented.  I drove my car and received a parking ticket during that time. Since I did not have flu-like symptoms and felt fine for 24 hours directly following the vaccine, I thought I was fine. It actually scares me that I drove my car and that this could happen to others.  I was back to normal 4-5 hours after symptoms started, and still had hazy to no recollection of the afternoon. I had to piece together the conversations and interactions the following day. I had a headache the following day and was tired.

Patient came to Vaccination Clinic to receive first dose of Pfizer vaccine on 3/18/2021. Patient has a medical history of Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome, Mast Cell Activation Syndrome, POTS (Postural Orthostatic Tachycardic Syndrome). Patient received approval from her doctor and specialists to receive Pfizer vaccine. The patient gave verbal consent to receive the Pfizer vaccine and was vaccinated at 1431. The patient was given an observation time of 30 minutes with EMT. At 1505, the patient reported experiencing tingling in the back of her throat. The patient presented with patchy erythema on chest and neck. The patient was brought into the exam room at 1510 and proceeded to lay down on exam table. At this time, the patient's vitals were taken by RN and found to be within normal limits (BP 115/90, HR 88 BPM, RR 15/min). The patient denied difficulty breathing. She reported feeling minor dizziness and minor itching of neck and arms. The patient's vitals were reassessed as the Lead RN drew up 50 mg/1 mL of IM Benadryl. The patient's vitals at 1518 were: BP 120/85, HR 80 BPM, RR 16/min. The patient remained A&Ox4. The patient was given 50mg of IM Benadryl at 1520 in the left anterolateral region. At 1530, Patient's vitals were: BP 117/80, HR 73 BPM, RR 12/min. At this time, the patient verbalized relief of itching in neck and arms. Upon assessment, the patient's erythema on neck and chest had resolved. At 1537, the patient sat up with her feet dangling below her, her vitals were as follows: BP 132/98, HR 73 BPM, RR 13/min. The patient reported "feeling better" and requested to use the restroom. An RN followed the patient to the restroom. Patient's gait was steady and she denied any dizziness or lightheadedness. Lead nurse educated patient on side effects of Benadryl, including drowsiness. At 1544, the patient requested to drive herself home. She was escorted to her car by lead RN. Patient drove herself home AMA at 1547.
HISTORY: Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome, Mast Cell Activation Syndrome, POTS (Postural Orthostatic Tachycardic Syndrome)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The day of the shot, we noticed significant swelling in my neck on the right of center.  The swelling has maintained its size for now six weeks and one day.  I have a dull numbness in my 2-3 smaller toes of my left foot.  Sometimes I feel this numbness in my right foot, but not always.  My left arm and two smallest fingers also feel funny.  There is a dull pain in my left arm and dull numbness in my left smaller fingers.  The outside of my left leg also at times shares this numb feeling.  On the day I got the shot I immediately felt like I had a dose of caffeine, though that feeling passed after a couple of hours.  It did not feel significant enough to keep me from driving or leaving the facility, but it was noticeable. I experienced diarrhea for about a week and a half. For the first week after the shot I alternated nights of not being able to stay still sleeping, keeping me awake almost the entire night, 3 of the first 6 nights.  I visited my family doctor within one week of the first shot.  He advised me not to get the second shot and made note of the swelling in my neck. I visited him at five weeks because the swelling in my neck and numb feeling has not changed.  He scheduled a CT Scan which has been scheduled.
LAB_DATA: CT Scan scheduled. Blood test taken, results  pending doctor's consultation.
